code.desc: Order to connect a reefer container to a reefer point.

code.title: Bill of exchange
code.desc: Document/message, issued and signed in conformity with the applicable legislation, which contains an unconditional order whereby the drawer directs the drawee to pay a definite sum of money to the payee or to his order, on demand or at a definite time, against the surrender of the document itself.

code.title: Promissory note
code.desc: Document/message, issued and signed in conformity with the applicable legislation, which contains an unconditional promise whereby the maker undertakes to pay a definite sum of money to the payee or to his order, on demand or at a definite time, against the surrender of the document itself.

code.title: Statement of account message
code.desc: Usage of STATAC-message.

code.title: Direct delivery (transport)
code.desc: Document/message ordering the direct delivery of goods/consignment from one means of transport into another means of transport in one movement.

code.title: WCO second step of two-step export declaration
code.desc: Second part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs export procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

code.title: WCO one-step import declaration
code.desc: Single step declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

code.title: WCO first step of two-step import declaration
code.desc: First part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

code.title: WCO second step of two-step import declaration
code.desc: Second part of a simplified declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs by which goods are declared for Customs import procedure based on the 1999 Kyoto Convention.

code.title: Previous transport document
code.desc: Identification of the previous transport document.

code.title: Insurance certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued to the insured certifying that insurance has been effected and that a policy has been issued. Such a certificate for a particular cargo is primarily used when good are insured under the terms of a floating or an open policy; at the request of the insured it can be exchanged for a policy.

code.title: Special requirements permit related to the transport of cargo
code.desc: A permit related to a transport document granting the transport of cargo under the conditions as specifically required.

code.title: Dangerous Goods Notification for Tanker vessel
code.desc: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying liquid cargo in bulk.

code.title: Dangerous Goods Notification for non-tanker vessel
code.desc: Dangerous Goods Notification for a vessel carrying cargo other than bulk liquid cargo.

code.title: WCO Conveyance Arrival Report
code.desc: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance arriving in a Customs territory.

code.title: WCO Conveyance Departure Report
code.desc: Declaration, in accordance with the WCO Customs Data Model, to Customs regarding the conveyance departing a Customs territory.

code.title: Accounting voucher
code.desc: A document/message justifying an accounting entry.

code.title: Insurance policy
code.desc: Document/message issued by the insurer evidencing an agreement to insure and containing the conditions of the agreement concluded whereby the insurer undertakes for a specific fee to indemnify the insured for the losses arising out of the perils and accidents specified in the contract.

code.title: Insurance declaration sheet (bordereau)
code.desc: A document/message used when an insured reports to his insurer details of individual shipments which are covered by an insurance contract - an open cover or a floating policy - between the parties.

code.title: Insurer's invoice
code.desc: Document/message issued by an insurer specifying the cost of an insurance which has been effected and claiming payment therefore.

code.title: Cover note
code.desc: Document/message issued by an insurer (insurance broker, agent, etc.) to notify the insured that his insurance have been carried out.

code.title: Forwarding instructions
code.desc: Document/message issued to a freight forwarder, giving instructions regarding the action to be taken by the forwarder for the forwarding of goods described therein.

code.title: Forwarder's advice to import agent
code.desc: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder in an exporting country advising his counterpart in an importing country about the forwarding of goods described therein.

code.title: Forwarder's advice to exporter
code.desc: Document/message issued by a freight forwarder informing an exporter of the action taken in fulfillment of instructions received.

code.title: Forwarder's invoice
code.desc: Invoice issued by a freight forwarder specifying services rendered and costs incurred and claiming payment therefore.

code.title: Forwarder's certificate of receipt
code.desc: Non-negotiable document issued by a forwarder to certify that he has assumed control of a specified consignment, with irrevocable instructions to send it to the consignee indicated in the document or to hold it at his disposal. E.g. FIATA-FCR.

code.title: Shipping note
code.desc: (1123) Document/message provided by the shipper or his agent to the carrier, multimodal transport operator, terminal or other receiving authority, giving information about export consignments offered for transport, and providing for the necessary receipts and declarations of liability. Sometimes a multipurpose cargo handling document also fulfilling the functions of document 632, 633, 650 and 655.

code.title: Forwarder's warehouse receipt
code.desc: Document/message issued by a forwarder acting as Warehouse Keeper acknowledging receipt of goods placed in a warehouse, and stating or referring to the conditions which govern the warehousing and the release of goods. The document contains detailed provisions regarding the rights of holders-by-endorsement, transfer of ownership, etc. E.g. FIATA-FWR.

code.title: Goods receipt
code.desc: Document/message to acknowledge the receipt of goods and in addition may indicate receiving conditions.

code.title: Port charges documents
code.desc: Documents/messages specifying services rendered, storage and handling costs, demurrage and other charges due to the owner of goods described therein.

code.title: Warehouse warrant
code.desc: Negotiable receipt document, issued by a Warehouse Keeper to a person placing goods in a warehouse and conferring title to the goods stored.

code.title: Delivery order
code.desc: Document/message issued by a party entitled to authorize the release of goods specified therein to a named consignee, to be retained by the custodian of the goods.

code.title: Handling order
code.desc: Document/message issued by a cargo handling organization (port administration, terminal operator, etc.) for the removal or other handling of goods under their care.

code.title: Gate pass
code.desc: Document/message authorizing goods specified therein to be brought out of a fenced-in port or terminal area.

code.title: Waybill
code.desc: Non-negotiable document evidencing the contract for the transport of cargo.

code.title: Universal (multipurpose) transport document
code.desc: Document/message evidencing a contract of carriage covering the movement of goods by any mode of transport, or combination of modes, for national as well as international transport, under any applicable international convention or national law and under the conditions of carriage of any carrier or transport operator undertaking or arranging the transport referred to in the document.

code.title: Goods receipt, carriage
code.desc: Document/message issued by a carrier or a carrier's agent, acknowledging receipt for carriage of goods specified therein on conditions stated or referred to in the document, enabling the carrier to issue a transport document.

code.title: House waybill
code.desc: The document made out by an agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the shipper and the agent/consolidator for the arrangement of carriage of goods.

code.title: Master bill of lading
code.desc: A bill of lading issued by the master of a vessel (in actuality the owner or charterer of the vessel). It could cover a number of house bills.

code.title: Bill of lading
code.desc: Negotiable document/message which evidences a contract of carriage by sea and the taking over or loading of goods by carrier, and by which carrier undertakes to deliver goods against surrender of the document. A provision in the document that goods are to be delivered to the order of a named person, or to order, or to bearer, constitutes such an undertaking.

code.title: Bill of lading original
code.desc: The original of the bill of lading issued by a transport company. When issued by the maritime industry it could signify ownership of the cargo.

code.title: Bill of lading copy
code.desc: A copy of the bill of lading issued by a transport company.

code.title: Empty container bill
code.desc: Bill of lading indicating an empty container.

code.title: Tanker bill of lading
code.desc: Document which evidences a transport of liquid bulk cargo.

code.title: Sea waybill
code.desc: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

code.title: Inland waterway bill of lading
code.desc: Negotiable transport document made out to a named person, to order or to bearer, signed by the carrier and handed to the sender after receipt of the goods.

code.title: Non-negotiable maritime transport document (generic)
code.desc: Non-negotiable document which evidences a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the carrier, and by which the carrier undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document. E.g. Sea waybill. Remark: Synonymous with "straight" or "non-negotiable Bill of lading" used in certain countries, e.g. Canada.

code.title: Mate's receipt
code.desc: Document/message issued by a ship's officer to acknowledge that a specified consignment has been received on board a vessel, and the apparent condition of the goods; enabling the carrier to issue a Bill of lading.

code.title: House bill of lading
code.desc: The bill of lading issued not by the carrier but by the freight forwarder/consolidator known by the carrier.

code.title: Letter of indemnity for non-surrender of bill of lading
code.desc: Document/message issued by a commercial party or a bank of an insurance company accepting responsibility to the beneficiary of the indemnity in accordance with the terms thereof.

code.title: Forwarder's bill of lading
code.desc: Non-negotiable document issued by a freight forwarder evidencing a contract for the carriage of goods by sea and the taking over or loading of the goods by the freight forwarder, and by which the freight forwarder undertakes to deliver the goods to the consignee named in the document.

code.title: Rail consignment note (generic term)
code.desc: Transport document constituting a contract for the carriage of goods between the sender and the carrier (the railway). For international rail traffic, this document must conform to the model prescribed by the international conventions concerning carriage of goods by rail, e.g. CIM Convention, SMGS Convention.

code.title: Road list-SMGS
code.desc: Accounting document, one copy of which is drawn up for each consignment note; it accompanies the consignment over the whole route and is a rail transport document.

code.title: Escort official recognition
code.desc: Document/message which gives right to the owner to exert all functions normally transferred to a guard in a train by which an escorted consignment is transported.

code.title: Recharging document
code.desc: Fictitious transport document regarding a previous transport, enabling a carrier's agent to give to another carrier's agent (in a different country) the possibility to collect charges relating to the original transport (rail environment).

code.title: Road consignment note
code.desc: Transport document/message which evidences a contract between a carrier and a sender for the carriage of goods by road (generic term). Remark: For international road traffic, this document must contain at least the particulars prescribed by the convention on the contract for the international carriage of goods by road (CMR).

code.title: Air waybill
code.desc: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the shipper which evidences the contract between the shipper and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) and which is identified by the airline prefix issuing the document plus a serial (IATA).

code.title: Master air waybill
code.desc: Document/message made out by or on behalf of the agent/consolidator which evidences the contract between the agent/consolidator and carrier(s) for carriage of goods over routes of the carrier(s) for a consignment consisting of goods originated by more than one shipper (IATA).

code.title: Substitute air waybill
code.desc: A temporary air waybill which contains only limited information because of the absence of the original.

code.title: Crew's effects declaration
code.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding the personal effects of crew members aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 4.

code.title: Passenger list
code.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding passengers aboard the conveyance; equivalent to IMO FAL 6.

code.title: Delivery notice (rail transport)
code.desc: Document/message created by the consignor or by the departure station, joined to the transport or sent to the consignee, giving the possibility to the consignee or the arrival station to attest the delivery of the goods. The document must be returned to the consignor or to the departure station.

code.title: Despatch note (post parcels)
code.desc: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU convention, is to accompany post parcels.

code.title: Multimodal/combined transport document (generic)
code.desc: A transport document used when more than one mode of transportation is involved in the movement of cargo. It is a contract of carriage and receipt of the cargo for a multimodal transport. It indicates the place where the responsible transport company in the move takes responsibility for the cargo, the place where the responsibility of this transport company in the move ends and the conveyances involved.

code.title: Through bill of lading
code.desc: Bill of lading which evidences a contract of carriage from one place to another in separate stages of which at least one stage is a sea transit, and by which the issuing carrier accepts responsibility for the carriage as set forth in the through bill of lading.

code.title: Forwarder's certificate of transport
code.desc: Negotiable document/message issued by a forwarder to certify that he has taken charge of a specified consignment for despatch and delivery in accordance with the consignor's instructions, as indicated in the document, and that he accepts responsibility for delivery of the goods to the holder of the document through the intermediary of a delivery agent of his choice. E.g. FIATA-FCT.

code.title: Combined transport document (generic)
code.desc: Negotiable or non-negotiable document evidencing a contract for the performance and/or procurement of performance of combined transport of goods and bearing on its face either the heading "Negotiable combined transport document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)" or the heading "Non-negotiable Combined Transport Document issued subject to Uniform Rules for a Combined Transport Document (ICC Brochure No. 298)".

code.title: Multimodal transport document (generic)
code.desc: Document/message which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract. (International Convention on Multimodal Transport of Goods).

code.title: Combined transport bill of lading/multimodal bill of lading
code.desc: Document which evidences a multimodal transport contract, the taking in charge of the goods by the multimodal transport operator, and an undertaking by him to deliver the goods in accordance with the terms of the contract.

code.title: Booking confirmation
code.desc: Document/message issued by a carrier to confirm that space has been reserved for a consignment in means of transport.

code.title: Calling forward notice
code.desc: Instructions for release or delivery of goods.

code.title: Freight invoice
code.desc: Document/message issued by a transport operation specifying freight costs and charges incurred for a transport operation and stating conditions of payment.

code.title: Arrival notice (goods)
code.desc: Notification from the carrier to the consignee in writing, by telephone or by any other means (express letter, message, telegram, etc.) informing him that a consignment addressed to him is being or will shortly be held at his disposal at a specified point in the place of destination.

code.title: Notice of circumstances preventing delivery (goods)
code.desc: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, as the case may be, the consignee, for instructions as to the disposal of the consignment when circumstances prevent delivery and the return of the goods has not been requested by the consignor in the transport document.

code.title: Notice of circumstances preventing transport (goods)
code.desc: Request made by the carrier to the sender, or, the consignee as the case may be, for instructions as to the disposal of the goods when circumstances prevent transport before departure or en route, after acceptance of the consignment concerned.

code.title: Delivery notice (goods)
code.desc: Notification in writing, sent by the carrier to the sender, to inform him at his request of the actual date of delivery of the goods.

code.title: Cargo manifest
code.desc: Listing of goods comprising the cargo carried in a means of transport or in a transport-unit. The cargo manifest gives the commercial particulars of the goods, such as transport document numbers, consignors, consignees, shipping marks, number and kind of packages and descriptions and quantities of the goods.

code.title: Freight manifest
code.desc: Document/message containing the same information as a cargo manifest, and additional details on freight amounts, charges, etc.

code.title: Bordereau
code.desc: Document/message used in road transport, listing the cargo carried on a road vehicle, often referring to appended copies of Road consignment note.

code.title: Container manifest (unit packing list)
code.desc: Document/message specifying the contents of particular freight containers or other transport units, prepared by the party responsible for their loading into the container or unit.

code.title: Charges note
code.desc: Document used by the rail organization to indicate freight charges or additional charges in each case where the departure station is not able to calculate the charges for the total voyage (e.g. tariff not yet updated, part of voyage not covered by the tariff). This document must be considered as joined to the transport.

code.title: Advice of collection
code.desc: (1030) Document that is joined to the transport or sent by separate means, giving to the departure rail organization the proof that the cash-on delivery amount has been encashed by the arrival rail organization before reimbursement of the consignor.

code.title: Safety of ship certificate
code.desc: Document certifying a ship's safety to a specified date.

code.title: Safety of radio certificate
code.desc: Document certifying the safety of a ship's radio facilities to a specified date.

code.title: Safety of equipment certificate
code.desc: Document certifying the safety of a ship's equipment to a specified date.

code.title: Civil liability for oil certificate
code.desc: Document declaring a ship owner's liability for oil propelling or carried on a vessel.

code.title: Loadline document
code.desc: Document specifying the limit of a ship's legal submersion under various conditions.

code.title: Derat document
code.desc: Document certifying that a ship is free of rats, valid to a specified date.

code.title: Maritime declaration of health
code.desc: Document certifying the health condition on board a vessel, valid to a specified date.

code.title: Certificate of registry
code.desc: Official certificate stating the vessel's registry.

code.title: Ship's stores declaration
code.desc: Declaration to Customs regarding the contents of the ship's stores (equivalent to IMO FAL 3) i.e. goods intended for consumption by passengers/crew on board vessels, aircraft or trains, whether or not sold or landed; goods necessary for operation/maintenance of conveyance, including fuel/lubricants, excluding spare parts/equipment (IMO).

code.title: Export licence, application for
code.desc: Application for a permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc.

code.title: Export licence
code.desc: Permit issued by a government authority permitting exportation of a specified commodity subject to specified conditions as quantity, country of destination, etc. Synonym: Embargo permit.

code.title: Exchange control declaration, export
code.desc: Document/message completed by an exporter/seller as a means whereby the competent body may control that the amount of foreign exchange accrued from a trade transaction is repatriated in accordance with the conditions of payment and exchange control regulations in force.

code.title: Despatch note model T
code.desc: European community transit declaration.

code.title: Despatch note model T1
code.desc: Transit declaration for goods circulating under internal community transit procedures (between European Union (EU) countries).

code.title: Despatch note model T2
code.desc: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country.

code.title: Control document T5
code.desc: Control document (export declaration) used particularly in case of re-sending without use with only VAT collection, refusal, unconformity with contract etc.

code.title: Re-sending consignment note
code.desc: Rail consignment note prepared by the consignor for the facilitation of an eventual return to the origin of the goods.

code.title: Despatch note model T2L
code.desc: Ascertainment that the declared goods were originally produced in an European Union (EU) country. May only be used for goods that are loaded on one single means of transport in one single departure point for one single delivery point.

code.title: Goods declaration for exportation
code.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for export Customs clearance, conforming to the layout key set out at Appendix I to Annex C.1 concerning outright exportation to the Kyoto convention (CCC). Within a Customs union, "for despatch" may have the same meaning as "for exportation".

code.title: Cargo declaration (departure)
code.desc: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

code.title: Application for goods control certificate
code.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Goods control certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

code.title: Goods control certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing the quality of the goods described therein, in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the importing country, or as specified in the contract.

code.title: Application for phytosanitary certificate
code.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by party requesting a Phytosanitary certificate to be issued.

code.title: Phytosanitary certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body in the exporting country evidencing that plants, fruit, or vegetables are free from disease and fit for consumption and giving details on fumigation or other treatment to which they may have been subjected.

code.title: Sanitary certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that alimentary and animal products, including dead animals, are fit for human consumption, and giving details, when relevant, of controls undertaken.

code.title: Veterinary certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued by the competent authority in the exporting country evidencing that live animals or birds are not infested or infected with disease, and giving details regarding their provenance, and of vaccinations and other treatment to which they have been subjected.

code.title: Application for inspection certificate
code.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by a party requesting an Inspection certificate to be issued in accordance with national or international standards, or conforming to legislation in the country in which it is required, or as specified in the contract.

code.title: Inspection certificate
code.desc: Document/message issued by a competent body evidencing that the goods described therein have been inspected in accordance with national or international standards, in conformity with legislation in the country in which the inspection is required, or as specified in the contract.

code.title: Certificate of origin, application for
code.desc: Document/message submitted to a competent body by an interested party requesting a Certificate of origin to be issued in accordance with relevant criteria, and on the basis of evidence of the origin of the goods.

code.title: Certificate of origin
code.desc: Document/message identifying goods, in which the authority or body authorized to issue it certifies expressly that the goods to which the certificate relates originate in a specific country. The word "country" may include a group of countries, a region or a part of a country. This certificate may also include a declaration by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person.

code.title: Declaration of origin
code.desc: Appropriate statement as to the origin of the goods, made in connection with their exportation by the manufacturer, producer, supplier, exporter or other competent person on the Commercial invoice or any other document relating to the goods (CCC).

code.title: Regional appellation certificate
code.desc: Certificate drawn up in accordance with the rules laid down by an authority or approved body, certifying that the goods described therein qualify for a designation specific to the given region (e.g. champagne, port wine, Parmesan cheese).

code.title: Preference certificate of origin
code.desc: Document/message describing a certificate of origin meeting the requirements for preferential treatment.

code.title: Certificate of origin form GSP
code.desc: Specific form of certificate of origin for goods qualifying for preferential treatment under the generalized system of preferences (includes a combined declaration of origin and certificate, form A).

code.title: Consular invoice
code.desc: Document/message to be prepared by an exporter in his country and presented to a diplomatic representation of the importing country for endorsement and subsequently to be presented by the importer in connection with the import of the goods described therein.

code.title: Dangerous goods declaration
code.desc: (1115) Document/message issued by a consignor in accordance with applicable conventions or regulations, describing hazardous goods or materials for transport purposes, and stating that the latter have been packed and labelled in accordance with the provisions of the relevant conventions or regulations.

code.title: Statistical document, export
code.desc: Document/message in which an exporter provides information about exported goods required by the body responsible for the collection of international trade statistics.

code.title: INTRASTAT declaration
code.desc: Document/message in which a declarant provides information about goods required by the body responsible for the collection of trade statistics.

code.title: Delivery verification certificate
code.desc: Document/message whereby an official authority (Customs or governmental) certifies that goods have been delivered.

code.title: Import licence, application for
code.desc: Document/message in which an interested party applies to the competent body for authorization to import either a limited quantity of articles subject to import restrictions, or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, and specifies the kind of articles, their origin and value, etc.

code.title: Import licence
code.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body in accordance with import regulations in force, by which authorization is granted to a named party to import either a limited quantity of designated articles or an unlimited quantity of such articles during a limited period, under conditions specified in the document.

code.title: Customs declaration without commercial detail
code.desc: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the commercial detail section of the message.

code.title: Customs declaration with commercial and item detail
code.desc: CUSDEC transmission that includes data from both the commercial detail and item detail sections of the message.

code.title: Customs declaration without item detail
code.desc: CUSDEC transmission that does not include data from the item detail section of the message.

code.title: Related document
code.desc: Document that has a relationship with the stated document/message.

code.title: Receipt (Customs)
code.desc: Receipt for Customs duty/tax/fee paid.

code.title: Application for exchange allocation
code.desc: Document/message whereby an importer/buyer requests the competent body to allocate an amount of foreign exchange to be transferred to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

code.title: Foreign exchange permit
code.desc: Document/message issued by the competent body authorizing an importer/buyer to transfer an amount of foreign exchange to an exporter/seller in payment for goods.

code.title: Exchange control declaration (import)
code.desc: Document/message completed by an importer/buyer as a means for the competent body to control that a trade transaction for which foreign exchange has been allocated has been executed and that money has been transferred in accordance with the conditions of payment and the exchange control regulations in force.

code.title: Goods declaration for importation
code.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance [sister entry of 830].

code.title: Goods declaration for home use
code.desc: Document/message by which goods are declared for import Customs clearance according to Annex B.1 (concerning clearance for home use) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

code.title: Customs immediate release declaration
code.desc: Document/message issued by an importer notifying Customs that goods have been removed from an importing means of transport to the importer's premises under a Customs- approved arrangement for immediate release, or requesting authorization to do so.

code.title: Customs delivery note
code.desc: Document/message whereby a Customs authority releases goods under its control to be placed at the disposal of the party concerned. Synonym: Customs release note.

code.title: Cargo declaration (arrival)
code.desc: Generic term, sometimes referred to as Freight declaration, applied to the documents providing the particulars required by the Customs concerning the cargo (freight) carried by commercial means of transport (CCC).

code.title: Value declaration
code.desc: Document/message in which a declarant (importer) states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, any relationship with the trading partner, etc., for the purpose of determining the Customs value of goods imported.

code.title: Customs invoice
code.desc: Document/message required by the Customs in an importing country in which an exporter states the invoice or other price (e.g. selling price, price of identical goods), and specifies costs for freight, insurance and packing, etc., terms of delivery and payment, for the purpose of determining the Customs value in the importing country of goods consigned to that country.

code.title: Customs declaration (post parcels)
code.desc: Document/message which, according to Article 106 of the "Agreement concerning Postal Parcels" under the UPU Convention, must accompany post parcels and in which the contents of such parcels are specified.

code.title: Tax declaration (value added tax)
code.desc: Document/message in which an importer states the pertinent information required by the competent body for assessment of value-added tax.

code.title: Tax declaration (general)
code.desc: Document/message containing a general tax declaration.

code.title: Tax demand
code.desc: Document/message containing the demand of tax.

code.title: Embargo permit
code.desc: Document/message giving the permission to export specified goods.

code.title: Goods declaration for Customs transit
code.desc: Document/message by which the sender declares goods for Customs transit according to Annex E.1 (concerning Customs transit) to the Kyoto convention (CCC).

code.title: TIF form
code.desc: International Customs transit document by which the sender declares goods for carriage by rail in accordance with the provisions of the 1952 International Convention to facilitate the crossing of frontiers for goods carried by rail (TIF Convention of UIC).

code.title: TIR carnet
code.desc: International Customs document (International Transit by Road), issued by a guaranteeing association approved by the Customs authorities, under the cover of which goods are carried, in most cases under Customs seal, in road vehicles and/or containers in compliance with the requirements of the Customs TIR Convention of the International Transport of Goods under cover of TIR Carnets (UN/ECE).

code.title: EC carnet
code.desc: EC customs transit document issued by EC customs authorities for transit and/or temporary user of goods within the EC.

code.title: EUR 1 certificate of origin
code.desc: Customs certificate used in preferential goods interchanges between EC countries and EC external countries.

code.title: ATA carnet
code.desc: International Customs document (Admission Temporaire / Temporary Admission) which, issued under the terms of the ATA Convention (1961), incorporates an internationally valid guarantee and may be used, in lieu of national Customs documents and as security for import duties and taxes, to cover the temporary admission of goods and, where appropriate, the transit of goods. If accepted for controlling the temporary export and reimport of goods, international guarantee does not apply (CCC).

code.title: Single administrative document
code.desc: A set of documents, replacing the various (national) forms for Customs declaration within the EC, implemented on 01-01-1988.

code.title: General response (Customs)
code.desc: General response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

code.title: Document response (Customs)
code.desc: Document response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

code.title: Error response (Customs)
code.desc: Error response message to permit the transfer of data from Customs to the transmitter of the previous message.

code.title: Package response (Customs)

code.title: CCYYP-CCYYP

code.title: CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM

code.title: Pager
code.desc: Identifies that the communication number is for a pager.

code.desc: The international telephone switchboard number.

code.title: National telephone direct line
code.desc: The national telephone direct line number.

code.title: National telephone switchboard
code.desc: The national telephone switchboard number.

code.title: Place of terms of delivery
code.desc: (3018) Point or port of departure, shipment or destination, as required under the applicable terms of delivery, e.g. Incoterms.

code.title: Payment location
code.desc: [3109] To identify the place where the payment has been or should be made.

code.title: Tare check place
code.desc: Place where equipment tare has been or must be checked for official assessment.

code.title: Goods receipt place
code.desc: Place at which the goods have been received.

code.title: Place of departure
code.desc: (3214) Port, airport or other location from which a means of transport or transport equipment is scheduled to depart or has departed.

code.title: Ward bed
code.desc: A bed in a ward.

code.title: Place of delivery
code.desc: (3246) Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

code.title: Place of destination
code.desc: Port, airport or other location to which a means of transport or transport equipment is destined.

code.title: Place of loading
code.desc: [3334] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are loaded on to the means of transport being used for their carriage.

code.title: Place of acceptance
code.desc: [3348] Place where the goods are taken over by the carrier.

code.title: Place of discharge
code.desc: [3392] Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which goods are unloaded from the means of transport having been used for their carriage.

code.title: Port of discharge
code.desc: Port at which the goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

code.title: Place of transhipment
code.desc: [3424] Place where goods are to be or have been transferred from one means of transport to another during the course of one transport operation.

code.title: Goods item storage location
code.desc: [3385] To identify the place where a goods item is located.

code.title: Place of transfer responsibility
code.desc: Place where the responsibility is transferred.

code.title: Place of transfer of ownership
code.desc: Place where the ownership of the goods is transferred.

code.title: Border crossing place
code.desc: Place where goods are transported across a country border.

code.title: Warehouse
code.desc: [3156] Warehouse where a particular consignment is to be or has been stored.

code.title: Factory/plant
code.desc: Factory/plant relevant for a particular consignment.

code.title: Place of ultimate destination of goods
code.desc: Place where goods will ultimately be delivered.

code.title: Terms of sale place
code.desc: Place of departure, shipment or destination as specified in the terms of sale agreed between the parties.

code.title: Customs clearance location
code.desc: [3080] Place at which Customs clearance should or has taken place.

code.title: Port of release
code.desc: Port where goods are released from Customs custody.

code.title: Port of entry
code.desc: Port where final documentation is filed for Customs Entry processing.

code.title: Country
code.desc: Country relevant for a particular transaction.

code.title: City
code.desc: City or town relevant for a particular transaction or consignment.

code.title: Country of origin
code.desc: [3239] To identify the country in which the goods have been produced or manufactured, according to criteria laid down for the application of the Customs tariff or quantitative restrictions, or any measure related to trade.

code.title: Country of destination of goods
code.desc: Country to which the goods are to be delivered.

code.title: Railway station
code.desc: Name or identification of a railway station/yard relevant to a particular consignment.

code.title: Country of source
code.desc: Country in which raw material or components were originally produced prior to manufacture or assembly in another country.

code.title: Building
code.desc: A building or part thereof relevant to a particular consignment or transaction.

code.title: Beginning of chargeable section
code.desc: First rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

code.title: Baseport of discharge
code.desc: [3356] Place at which the cargo is discharged or unloaded from a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be discharged from the main means of transport at this place or port.

code.title: Baseport of loading
code.desc: [3322] Place at which the cargo is loaded on a means of transport according to the transport contract. The goods may or may not be loaded on the main means of transport at this place or port.

code.title: Exportation country
code.desc: [3220] Country from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Synonym: Country whence consigned. Country of despatch: Country from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

code.title: Country of ultimate destination
code.desc: (3216) Country known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final country to which the goods are to be delivered.

code.title: Consignment final exportation country
code.desc: [3331] To identify the country from which goods have been or will be consigned prior to final importation.

code.title: Consignment first destination country
code.desc: [3219] To identify the country where a consignment is off-loaded from the means of transport used for the original exportation.

code.title: Country of production
code.desc: Country where item has been or will be produced.

code.title: Country of trading
code.desc: Country where item has been or will be traded.

code.title: Consignment entry customs office location
code.desc: [3089] To identify the customs office at which the goods enter the customs territory of destination.

code.title: Consignment exit customs office location
code.desc: [3097] To identify the customs office at which the goods leave or are intended to leave the customs territory of despatch.

code.title: Place of Customs examination
code.desc: Place where Customs undertakes a physical inspection of goods to satisfy themselves that the goods' nature, origin, condition, quantity and value are in accordance with the particulars furnished on the goods declaration (CCC).

code.title: Place of authentication of document
code.desc: (3410) Place where document is signed or otherwise authenticated. Synonym: Place of issue of document.

code.title: Customs office of destination (transit)
code.desc: (3086) Customs office at which a transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Customs office of transit termination.

code.title: Region of despatch
code.desc: Region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

code.title: Region of destination
code.desc: Region known to the consignor or his agent at the time of despatch to be the final region to which the goods are to be delivered.

code.title: Region of production
code.desc: Region where item has been or will be produced.

code.title: Transit country
code.desc: [3263] Country through which a goods or passengers are routed between the country of original departure and final destination.

code.title: Transit customs office location
code.desc: [3107] To identify the customs office which is responsible for transit formalities en-route.

code.title: Country of invalid transit guarantee
code.desc: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is not valid.

code.title: Country of destination (transit)
code.desc: Country at which a Customs transit operation is terminated. Synonym: Country of transit termination.

code.title: Charge and freight due from
code.desc: Place or point from which charges and freight are charged.

code.title: Manufacturing department
code.desc: A department within the manufacturing area (e.g. lacquering, assembly).

code.title: Freight charge payable to location
code.desc: [3102] Name of a place to which a transport charges tariff applies or where freight and other related charges are to be or have been incurred.

code.title: End of chargeable section
code.desc: Last rail station in a predefined section of the chargeable voyage. A complete voyage may be divided in sections, even within one country, that are separately chargeable using different tariff rules (split tariffs).

code.title: Place of payment
code.desc: Name of the location at which freight and charges for main transport are payable.

code.title: Full track loading or unloading
code.desc: Identification of the station proceeding to the loading or unloading of a rail wagon on a full track site. (Used only when a rail station is obliged to transfer the load on another wagon for technical reasons - e.g. damage).

code.title: Place of loss
code.desc: To identify the location where the loss occurred.

code.title: Place of arrival
code.desc: Place at which the transport means arrives.

code.title: Next port of call
code.desc: Next port which the vessel is going to call upon.

code.title: On-carriage port
code.desc: Port of discharge at which the cargo is discharged from the vessel, used for transport after the main transport (transit port).

code.title: Sub-project location
code.desc: A place at which works occur referring to a sub-project.

code.title: First optional place of discharge
code.desc: The first optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

code.title: Final port or place of discharge
code.desc: Name of the seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place at which the goods (cargo) are finally (to be) unloaded from the means of transport used for their carriage according to the transport contract.

code.title: Express railway station
code.desc: Railway station offering express transportation services.

code.title: Mixed cargo railway station
code.desc: Railway station offering mixed cargo transportation services .

code.title: Second optional place of discharge
code.desc: The second optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of shipper.

code.title: Next non-discharge port of call
code.desc: A code to identify the next port of call for a vessel where no cargo will be discharged.

code.title: Third optional place of discharge
code.desc: The third optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

code.title: Reconsolidation point
code.desc: A place where cargo is reconsolidated.

code.title: Fourth optional place of discharge
code.desc: The fourth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

code.title: Bill of lading release office
code.desc: A location where bills of lading are released to customers.

code.title: Transhipment excluding this place
code.desc: Place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is not authorised.

code.title: Transhipment limited to this place
code.desc: Only place/location where a transhipment from a means of transport to another means of transport is authorised.

code.title: Original port of loading
code.desc: The port where the goods were first loaded on a vessel.

code.title: First port of call - non-discharging
code.desc: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will not be discharging cargoes.

code.title: First port of call - discharging
code.desc: Port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the 'last place/port of call of conveyance' and where a conveyance will be discharging cargoes.

code.title: Place/port of first entry
code.desc: Place or port where final documentation is filed for Customs entry processing.

code.title: Place of despatch
code.desc: Place at which the goods are taken over for carriage (operational term), if different from the transport contract place of acceptance (see: 10). Synonym: Place of origin of carriage.

code.title: Fifth optional place of discharge
code.desc: The fifth optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the transport document where cargo can be discharged at the option of the shipper.

code.title: Pre-carriage port
code.desc: Port of loading at which the cargo is loaded on the pre- carriage vessel used for the transport prior to the main transport.

code.title: Place of delivery (by on carriage)
code.desc: Place to which the goods are to be finally delivered.

code.title: Transport contract place of acceptance
code.desc: Place at which the goods are taken over by the carrier according to the contract of carriage.

code.title: Transport contract place of destination
code.desc: Place to which the goods are destined.

code.title: Country of valid transit guarantee
code.desc: Country in which the security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is valid.

code.title: Place/port of conveyance initial arrival
code.desc: Place/port in the country of destination where the conveyance initially arrives from the "Last place/port of call of conveyance" (125).

code.title: Place of receipt
code.desc: Identification of the location at which the cargo is actually received.

code.title: Place of registration
code.desc: Place where the registration occurs.

code.title: Special treatment place
code.desc: Place where one or more special treatments have happened or must happen.

code.title: Place of document issue
code.desc: The place or location where a document is issued.

code.title: Routing
code.desc: Indication of a routing place.

code.title: Station of application of additional costs
code.desc: Rail station where, according to the transport contract, some chargeable operations must happen (re-weighting, re-fixing of the load, control on equipment and on consignment, etc.).

code.title: Previous port of call
code.desc: Previous port which the vessel has called upon.

code.title: Sailing destination area
code.desc: Geographical area to which the vessel's trip is destined.

code.title: Place of lodgement of documents
code.desc: Customs station where, required documents for Customs declarations, have been lodged.

code.title: Optional place of discharge
code.desc: The optional place or port of discharge as mentioned on the bill of lading where cargo is discharged at the option of the shipper.

code.title: Place of empty equipment despatch
code.desc: The location from which empty equipment is despatched.

code.title: Place of empty equipment return
code.desc: The location to which empty equipment is returned.

code.title: Place/port of warehouse entry
code.desc: Location (e.g. district) within a Customs territory where a warehouse entry was filed to enter merchandise into a Customs bonded warehouse.

code.title: Country of first sale
code.desc: Name of country where firstly a sale took place.

code.title: Country of purchase
code.desc: [3394] Country where the importer's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

code.title: Place of transfer
code.desc: Place at which goods are transferred from one carrier to another (contractual term).

code.title: Place of deconsolidation
code.desc: Place where a large consignment is de-grouped into smaller consignments.

code.title: Place of consumption
code.desc: Place/location where goods enter the marketplace (commerce) of the importing country.

code.title: Region of origin
code.desc: Region in which the goods have been produced or manufactured according to the criteria laid down for the purposes of the application of the Customs tariff, of quantitative restrictions or of any other measures related to trade (see: 3238).

code.title: Place of consolidation
code.desc: Place where smaller consignments of goods are grouped together into a large consignment to be transported as a larger unit.

code.title: Rate combination point
code.desc: Point over which sector rates are combined.

code.title: Place of prolongation decision of delivery delay
code.desc: Place where it has been decided to prolong the delivery delay.

code.title: Recharging place/location
code.desc: Place/location where a consignment has been changed of destination and is subject to a recharge note. (Complementary orders to modify the routing of the transport may be given, upon which a new charge calculation may be applied by the carrier).

code.title: Customs office of despatch
code.desc: Customs office from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

code.title: Region of equipment availability
code.desc: Region in which a piece of equipment is requested to be made available for on-hire.

code.title: Country of despatch
code.desc: Country from which goods are despatched within a Customs union.

code.title: Customs office of export
code.desc: Customs office from which goods are taken out of the Customs territory (CCC).

code.title: Free zone of export
code.desc: Foreign free zone (desc: see 1131 = 131) from which goods are exported to the country of importation.

code.title: Region of export/despatch
code.desc: Region from which the goods were initially exported to the importing country without any commercial transaction taking place in intermediate countries. Region of despatch: region from which goods are despatched between countries of a Customs union.

code.title: Place of collection
code.desc: Place where goods are to be or could be picked up (collected).

code.title: Customs office of departure
code.desc: Customs office at which a Customs transit operation commences (CCC).

code.title: Transit guarantee customs office location
code.desc: [3111] To identify the Customs office at which a security or guarantee for the movement of goods under a transit procedure is lodged.

code.title: Country of transhipment
code.desc: Country where goods are transferred under Customs control from the importing means of transport to the exporting means of transport within the area of one Customs office which is the office of both importation and exportation (CCC).

code.title: Country of sale
code.desc: [3116] Country where exporter's co-contractor is domiciled or has his business.

code.title: Customs office of destination
code.desc: Customs office where the goods are to be cleared (CCC).

code.title: Wagon-load railway station
code.desc: A railway station where rail wagons are loaded.

code.title: Siding
code.desc: A short railway track for loading or unloading rail wagons, or bypassing of trains, connected with a main track by switch.

code.title: Last place/port of call of conveyance
code.desc: Conveyance departed from this last foreign place/port of call to go to "Place/port of conveyance initial arrival" (87).

code.title: Country of previous Customs procedure
code.desc: Country in which the Customs declaration for the previous Customs procedure has been lodged.

code.title: Customs office of registration of previous Customs declaration
code.desc: Customs office where the previous Customs declaration has been lodged.

code.title: Participant sender location
code.desc: Place where a participant in the movement of goods is located and can be contacted.

code.title: Wage negotiation district
code.desc: The district to which workers belong for the purposes of union wage negotiation.

code.title: Place of ultimate destination of conveyance
code.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place to which a means of transport is ultimately destined.

code.title: Place of loading of empty equipment
code.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was loaded onto means of transport.

code.title: Place of discharge of empty equipment
code.desc: Seaport, airport, freight terminal, rail station or other place where empty equipment (e.g. containers) was unloaded from means of transport.

code.title: Region of delivery
code.desc: (3246) Region to which the goods are to be finally delivered under transport contract terms (operational term).

code.title: Petroleum warehouse
code.desc: Bonded petroleum warehouse or the supplier source.

code.title: Place of entry (Customs)
code.desc: Place at which the goods enter the Customs territory.

code.title: Living animals care place
code.desc: Place where living animal cares are provided.

code.title: Re-icing place
code.desc: Place where re-icing must be executed.

code.title: Weighting place
code.desc: Place where weight can be ascertained.

code.title: Marshalling yard
code.desc: Station where the wagons are disconnected and reconnected to form a new train.

code.title: Stopping station
code.desc: Station where the train must stop or is stopped for unexpected handling.

code.title: Loading dock
code.desc: Platform specially equipped for loading and unloading of rail wagons.

code.title: Port connection
code.desc: Track connecting a rail station to a dock.

code.title: Place of expiry
code.desc: Place where the documentary credit expires for presentation of required documents.

code.title: Place of negotiation
code.desc: Place where the documentary credit is to be presented for negotiation.

code.title: Claims payable place
code.desc: Place where insurance claims are payable.

code.title: Documentary credit available in
code.desc: Place where the documentary credit is available with any bank.

code.title: Transport means stowage location
code.desc: [8043] To identify a location on board a means of transport where specified goods or transport equipment has been or are to be stowed.

code.title: For transportation to
code.desc: Place/country where goods are to be transported to.

code.title: Loading on board/despatch/taking in charge at/from
code.desc: Place/country where goods have to be loaded on board, despatched or taken in charge.

code.title: Container stack position
code.desc: Stack position of a container at a terminal, depot or freight station.

code.title: Private box
code.desc: A private box used for pick-up and delivery of packages, e.g. of express packages.

code.title: Next port of discharge
code.desc: Next port at which goods are discharged from the vessel used for their transport.

code.title: Port of call
code.desc: Port where a vessel has called upon or will call upon.

code.title: Place/location of on-hire
code.desc: Place/location where an object is contracted for use.

code.title: Place/location of off-hire
code.desc: Place/location where an object's contract for use ends.

code.title: Other carriers terminal
code.desc: A carrier terminal belonging to a carrier other than the original carrier.

code.title: Country of Value Added Tax (VAT) jurisdiction
code.desc: The country governing the VAT regulation to which the transaction is subject.

code.title: Contact location
code.desc: The site where a contact is located.

code.title: Additional internal destination
code.desc: Any location within the consignee's premises where the goods are moved to.

code.title: Foreign port of call
code.desc: A code to identify the foreign port where the vessel calls at or will call at.

code.title: Maintenance location
code.desc: A location where maintenance has been or will be performed.

code.title: Place or location of sale
code.desc: Place or location at which the sale takes place.

code.title: Direct investment country
code.desc: Country in which a direct investment is made or withdrawn.

code.title: Berth
code.desc: Location in port where the vessel is berthed or moored.

code.title: Construction country
code.desc: Country in which the construction work is made.

code.title: Donation acting country
code.desc: Country acting in the donation of aid.

code.title: Payment transaction country
code.desc: Country of the foreign counterpart of the payment transaction.

code.title: Physical place of return of item
code.desc: Physical place at which the item is returned, i.e. the location where the supplier receives the item form the customer.

code.title: Relay port
code.desc: A location where cargo is transferred from one means of transport to another means of transport owned or operated by the same carrier under the same bill of lading.

code.title: Distributor
code.desc: A person or group acting explicitly as distributor of merchandise or goods.

code.title: Jobber

code.title: Manufacturer
code.desc: A company that produces goods from raw materials.

code.title: OEM (Original equipment manufacturer)

code.title: Resale

code.title: User

code.title: In patient
code.desc: A patient under the full time care of a hospital.

code.title: Electricity exchange

code.title: Information only

code.title: Special agreement for full loading transport

code.title: Normal tariff, full loading transport

code.title: Special tariff, full transport

code.desc: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved.

code.title: Transferable irrevocable documentary credit
code.desc: Written undertaking by a bank to pay a seller against stipulated documents that cannot be amended or cancelled without the consent of all parties involved and that can be transferred by the first beneficiary to one or more beneficiaries.

code.title: Irrevocable letter of credit-confirmed
code.desc: Letter of credit that cannot be cancelled or amended without agreement by all the parties involved, and carries the endorsement of both the issuing bank and its correspondent, guaranteeing payment of all drafts written against.

code.title: Letter of guarantee
code.desc: Any guarantee, bond or other payment undertaking given for the payment of money on presentation in conformity with the terms of the undertaking of a demand for payment and other documents specified.

code.desc: Letter of credit that can be cancelled or amended at any time by the issuing bank.

code.title: Irrevocable letter of credit unconfirmed
code.desc: Letter of credit that cannot be cancelled or amended before a specific date without agreement by all the parties involved, and carries no guarantee that a correspondent will honour drafts presented for payment.

code.title: Documentary collection (ICC)
code.desc: A collection in which the seller exchanges the delivery of the goods and any documents giving control of such goods for payment or upon promise of payment by acceptance of a commercial document. This type of collection involves financial and commercial documents. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

code.title: Documentary sight collection (ICC)
code.desc: A collection in which the commercial documents are delivered against immediate payment. International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) term.

code.title: Documentary collection with date of expiry (ICC)

code.title: Documentary collection: bill of exchange against acceptance

code.title: Documentary collection: bill of exchange against payment

code.title: Home-banking debit transfer
code.desc: A debit transfer initiated through home-banking.

code.title: Bank card
code.desc: Payment by means of a card issued by a bank or other financial institution.

code.title: Direct debit
code.desc: The amount is to be, or has been, directly debited to the customer's bank account.

code.title: Payment by postgiro
code.desc: A method for the transmission of funds through the postal system rather than through the banking system.

code.title: FR, norme 6 97-Telereglement CFONB (French Organisation for Banking Standards) - Option A
code.desc: A French standard procedure that allows a debtor to pay an amount due to a creditor. The creditor will forward it to its bank, which will collect the money on the bank account of the debtor.

code.title: Urgent commercial payment
code.desc: Payment order which requires guaranteed processing by the most appropriate means to ensure it occurs on the requested execution date, provided that it is issued to the ordered bank before the agreed cut-off time.

code.title: Urgent Treasury Payment
code.desc: Payment order or transfer which must be executed, by the most appropriate means, as urgently as possible and before urgent commercial payments.

code.title: Promissory note
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by one person to another, signed by the maker, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by the debtor
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the debtor to another person, signed by the debtor, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by the debtor and endorsed by a bank
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the debtor to another person, signed by the debtor and endorsed by a bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by the debtor and endorsed by a third party
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the debtor to another person, signed by the debtor and endorsed by a third party, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by a bank
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the bank to another person, signed by the bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by a bank and endorsed by another bank
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by the bank to another person, signed by the bank and endorsed by another bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by a third party
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by a third party to another person, signed by the third party, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Promissory note signed by a third party and endorsed by a bank
code.desc: Payment by an unconditional promise in writing made by a third party to another person, signed by the third party and endorsed by a bank, engaging to pay on demand or at a fixed or determinable future time a sum certain in money, to order or to bearer.

code.title: Bill drawn by the creditor on the debtor
code.desc: Bill drawn by the creditor on the debtor.

code.desc: Bill drawn by the creditor on a bank.

code.title: Bill drawn by the creditor, endorsed by another bank

code.title: Bill drawn by the creditor on a bank and endorsed by a third party

code.title: Bill drawn by the creditor on a third party

code.title: Not transferable banker's draft

code.title: Not transferable local cheque

code.title: Reference giro

code.title: Urgent giro
code.desc: Ordering customer tells the bank to use the bank service 'Urgent Giro' when transferring the payment. Used in Finnish national banking system.

code.title: Free format giro

code.title: Requested method for payment was not used

code.title: Clearing between partners

code.title: Mutually defined

code.title: Intra-company payment

code.title: Agreed settlement

code.title: Below specification goods

code.title: Invoice error

code.title: Deduction for late delivery

code.title: Advertising costs

code.title: Customs duties

code.desc: Telephone and postal costs deducted from payment.

code.title: Attorney fees

code.title: Taxes

code.title: Reclaimed deduction

code.title: See separate advice

code.title: Buyer refused to take delivery
code.desc: Buyer refused to take delivery.

code.title: Direct payment to seller

code.title: Buyer disagrees with due date
code.desc: Buyer disagrees with due date.

code.title: Goods not delivered

code.title: Late delivery
code.desc: Goods delivered too late.

code.title: Goods returned
code.desc: Buyer returned the goods to seller.

code.title: Invoice not received

code.title: Deducted discount

code.title: Discount beyond terms

code.title: See buyer's letter

code.title: Allowance/charge error

code.title: Substitute product

code.title: Terms of sale error
code.desc: Terms of sale not according to purchase order.

code.title: Required data missing

code.title: Wrong invoice
code.desc: Invoice issued to wrong party.

code.title: Duplicate invoice

code.title: Weight error

code.title: Additional charge not authorized

code.title: Incorrect discount

code.title: Price change

code.title: Variation

code.title: Offset

code.title: Settlement to agent

code.title: Cash discount

code.title: Delcredere costs

code.title: Early payment allowance adjustment

code.title: Incorrect due date for monetary amount

code.title: Wrong monetary amount resulting from incorrect free goods quantity

code.title: Temporary special promotion

code.title: Difference in tax rate

code.title: Quantity discount

code.title: Promotion discount
code.desc: Adjustment due to a promotion discount.

code.title: Cancellation deadline passed

code.title: Pricing discount

code.title: Treasury management service charge

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.
