code.desc: The assigned structure tag is requested.

code.title: All available status information
code.desc: All available status information is requested.

code.title: Delivery status of all back order articles
code.desc: Information on the delivery status of all articles on back order.

code.title: General status of all back order articles
code.desc: Information on the general status of all articles on back order.

code.title: Delivery status of all outstanding orders
code.desc: Information on the delivery status of all outstanding orders.

code.title: General status of all outstanding orders
code.desc: Information on the general status of all outstanding orders.

code.title: Delivery status of the specified order(s) or order line(s)
code.desc: Delivery status of each order(s) or order line(s) specified.

code.title: General status of the specified order(s) or order line(s)
code.desc: General status of each order(s) or order line(s) specified.

code.title: New
code.desc: The data is to be processed as new.

code.title: Add and replace
code.desc: The data contains new objects, which are to be added, and existing objects, which are to replace objects which have the same identifier.

code.title: Replace
code.desc: The data is to replace existing data which has the same identifier.

code.title: Delete
code.desc: The data identified is to be deleted.

code.title: None
code.desc: The data is not to be maintained.

code.title: Addition
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves addition.

code.title: Change
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves change.

code.title: Marked for deletion
code.desc: The item is marked for deletion in a future release.

code.title: Repair
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves repair.

code.title: Cleaning
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves cleaning.

code.title: Waste disposal
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves waste disposal.

code.title: Return of empty packages
code.desc: Maintenance operation involves return of empty packages.

code.title: In right condition
code.desc: The seal is in right condition.

code.title: Damaged
code.desc: The seal is damaged.

code.title: Missing
code.desc: A seal that is missing.

code.title: Broken
code.desc: Used to specify that the seal is broken.

code.title: Faulty electronic seal
code.desc: The electronic seal is faulty.

code.title: Destination charge totals
code.desc: Code to indicate total charges levied at destination.

code.title: Alternative currency amount
code.desc: The amount is expressed in alternate currency.

code.title: Total message amount
code.desc: The total amount of the message.

code.title: Invoices total amount summary
code.desc: The summary of a number of invoices' total amounts.

code.title: Amount for Customs purposes
code.desc: Number of monetary units expressed in a specified currency for Customs purposes (see: 5004).

code.title: Financial transaction amount
code.desc: Amount refers to financial transaction.

code.title: Total(s) of deferred items
code.desc: To specify the total(s) of all deferred items from one reinsurance account.

code.title: Total(s) of open cash claims
code.desc: To specify the total(s) of all open cash claims from one reinsurance account.

code.title: Reinsurance account balance
code.desc: To specify the result(s) of the reinsurance account calculation.

code.title: Prepaid totals
code.desc: Totals of prepaid freight and charges.

code.title: Collect totals
code.desc: Totals of collect freight and charges.

code.title: Valuation amounts
code.desc: Code to indicate valuation amounts.

code.title: Prepayment amount
code.desc: The amount paid or to be paid before a business transaction occurs.

code.title: Alternative currency total amount
code.desc: The total amount expressed in an alternate currency.

code.title: Documentary credit amount
code.desc: Value expressed in monetary terms of the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amounts covered: freight costs
code.desc: Freight costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amounts covered: insurance costs
code.desc: Insurance costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amounts covered: interest
code.desc: Interest on delayed or deferred payment is also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amounts covered: inspection costs
code.desc: Goods inspection costs are also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Part of documentary credit amount
code.desc: Part of documentary credit subject to sight, deferred or acceptance payment when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

code.title: Amount of note
code.desc: Amount of debit or credit note.

code.title: Hash total
code.desc: Total sum of amounts specified for control purposes.

code.title: Cumulative total, this period
code.desc: Totals to date.

code.title: Period total
code.desc: Totals this measurement period.

code.title: Cumulative total, preceding period
code.desc: Total to the end of last measurement period.

code.title: Total balance credit risk covered
code.desc: The total balance of factored invoices which are covered for credit risk.

code.title: Labour costs
code.desc: Identifying costs related to labour resource.

code.title: Business credit amount
code.desc: Monetary amount(s) associated with business credit information.

code.title: Project
code.desc: Indicates that the index relates to the whole project.

code.title: Group
code.desc: Indicates that the index relates to a group of work items.

code.title: Alternative
code.desc: Indicates that the index is an alternative.

code.title: VAT, 1st value
code.desc: First VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 1 to 3 different ways to set this value.

code.title: VAT, 2nd value
code.desc: Second VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 2 or 3 different ways to set this value.

code.title: VAT, 3rd value
code.desc: Third VAT value if, for the same rate of VAT, there are 3 different ways to set this value.

code.title: Additional royalties (Customs)
code.desc: Royalties relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

code.title: Adjusted amount
code.desc: The amount specified is the adjusted amount.

code.title: Amount reference currency
code.desc: The owing amount in the currency used as reference in the transaction.

code.title: Agreed charge
code.desc: Charges which parties agreed upon.

code.title: Allowance or charge amount
code.desc: Total amount of allowance or charge.

code.title: Amount due/amount payable
code.desc: Amount to be paid.

code.title: Amount in charge currency
code.desc: Indicates that the amount is based on the charged currency.

code.title: Amount paid
code.desc: Amount that has been paid.

code.title: Amount remitted
code.desc: Amount which was remitted (see remittance advice).

code.title: Amount subject to total monetary discount
code.desc: The amount is subject to a total monetary discount.

code.title: Amount target currency
code.desc: The amount in the currency in which the amount is paid or has to be paid.

code.title: Average ledger balance
code.desc: The addition of the balance all accounts divided by the number of accounts.

code.title: Bank release fee
code.desc: The fee that a bank charges for releasing monies.

code.title: Batch total
code.desc: The complete quantity of anything needed for or made in one operation or lot.

code.title: Brokerage
code.desc: Fee charged by a broker for acting on behalf of a third party.

code.title: Buying commission
code.desc: Commission paid by the importer to his/her agent for the service of representing him/her in the purchase.

code.title: Data value on carrier media (Customs)
code.desc: Value of data contained on the carrier media (e.g. magnetic tape).

code.title: Cash discount
code.desc: Cash discount given by the seller to the buyer.

code.title: Consignment cash on delivery amount
code.desc: [5017] Monetary amount to be paid at time of delivery.

code.title: Charge amount
code.desc: The amount of money charged for the provision of a service or product.

code.title: Charge summary total
code.desc: Code to indicate the total charges relating to a consignment.

code.title: Charge/allowance basis
code.desc: The amount specified is the basis for calculation of charges/allowance.

code.title: Charges collect fee
code.desc: The fee a party charges for collecting charges.

code.title: Charges in destination currency
code.desc: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

code.title: Collect charge summary total
code.desc: A summary total of collection charges.

code.title: Collect charges in destination currency
code.desc: Collect charges payable in the currency of the country of destination.

code.title: Collect freight charge including VAT
code.desc: This is the total amount that has to be collected from the consignee or other intermediary intervening party - Including VAT-.

code.title: Collect freight charge without VAT
code.desc: For legal accounting reasons the amount without VAT has to be announced, together with the amount of VAT.

code.title: Collect other charges due agent total
code.desc: The total of other charges that are due to the agent.

code.title: Collect taxes total
code.desc: The total amount of taxes to be collected.

code.title: Collected balance required
code.desc: A certain sum of money that must be kept in an account.

code.title: Container cost
code.desc: The cost of providing a container.

code.title: Converted amount
code.desc: The amount is converted from another currency.

code.title: Credit on consignment
code.desc: Credit deducted from the total invoice amount for the value of goods not included in a consignment but included in the invoice.

code.title: Invoice item amount
code.desc: (5068) Total sum charged in respect of a single Invoice item in accordance with the terms of delivery.

code.title: Invoice total amount
code.desc: [5214] Amount, debited by the seller and being the total of related article item amounts in a commercial invoice.

code.title: Goods item for customs declared value amount
code.desc: [5032] Amount declared for customs purposes of those goods in a consignment which are subject to the same customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

code.title: Assigned Customs value
code.desc: Goods value assigned by Customs.

code.title: Total cash payments received by factor
code.desc: Total allocated amount of cash payments received by a factor.

code.title: Consignment for customs total amount
code.desc: [5070] Total amount for customs purposes of all goods in a consignment, whether or not they are subject to the same customs procedure, and have the same tariff/statistical heading, country information and duty regime.

code.title: Goods item for carriage declared value amount
code.desc: [5036] Value, declared by the shipper or his agent solely for the purpose of varying the carrier's level of liability from that provided in the contract of carriage, in case of loss or damage to goods or delayed delivery.

code.title: Deductible after importation charges (Customs)
code.desc: Charges (e.g. construction, assembly, erection, maintenance or technical assistance) after importation, which are included in the total invoice price, that may be deducted to arrive at a Customs value.

code.title: Customs allowable deduction basis amount
code.desc: [5020] Allowable deductions from the price payable for calculating Customs value.

code.title: Delivery fee
code.desc: Fees incurred by delivery.

code.title: Deposit total
code.desc: The whole amount of money that one entrusts for safekeeping.

code.title: Development necessary for production of imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Value of engineering, development, artwork, design work and plans and sketches carried out elsewhere than in the Customs territory and necessary for the production of the imported goods.

code.title: Disbursements
code.desc: Amount of disbursements to be collected by the carrier according to the order given by the shipper.

code.title: Disbursements fee
code.desc: Fee charged for the collection of disbursements.

code.title: Discount amount
code.desc: (5014) The amount specified is the discount amount.

code.title: Discount amount due
code.desc: The amount of discount that is due.

code.title: Distribution service fee
code.desc: The fee charged for the provision of distribution services.

code.title: Duty amount
code.desc: The amount of duty.

code.title: Duty/tax/fee basis amount
code.desc: The amount specified is the basis for duty/tax or fee.

code.title: Equivalent amount
code.desc: This amount is equivalent to the amount to be transferred, but in another currency.

code.title: Fee amount
code.desc: The amount of a fee.

code.title: Fees paid year to date
code.desc: Payments made for goods thus far.

code.title: Final (posted) amount
code.desc: The amount posted to an account, finally, after charges/allowances.

code.title: Float (e.g. "cash float")
code.desc: The status of funds in the process of collection.

code.title: Total payments on account received by a factor
code.desc: Total unallocated amount of payments received by a factor.

code.title: FOB value
code.desc: Identifies the value of the shipment free on board, named port of shipment (see FOB Incoterm of ICC).

code.title: Freight charge
code.desc: Amount to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another, inclusive discounts, allowances, rebates, adjustment factors and additional cost relating to freight costs (UN/ECE Recommendation no 23).

code.title: Total indirect amount payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor
code.desc: Total indirect amount of payments made to a seller or his agent instead of to a factor.

code.title: Goods item total
code.desc: Net price x quantity for the line item.

code.title: Insurance amount
code.desc: Amount of insurance.

code.title: Insurance and transport charges (Customs)
code.desc: (5488)+(5290) Sum total of transport and insurance charges (CCC).

code.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
code.desc: (5488)+(5290) Insurance and transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

code.title: Consignment to importation location insurance amount
code.desc: [5488] Amount of premium payable to the insurance company to insure the goods to the port or place of importation.

code.title: Insurance charges incurred outside of Customs territory
code.desc: (5488) Insurance charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

code.title: Internal charges (Customs)
code.desc: Charges incurred within a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

code.title: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account
code.desc: Total amount of payments booked to the collateral account.

code.title: Amount to be paid in advance
code.desc: Amount which is to be paid before goods are delivered or the service is rendered.

code.title: Registered capital
code.desc: Registered amount of equity of a company.

code.title: Investable balance
code.desc: To put left over money in something offering profitable returns.

code.title: Invoice line item amount
code.desc: [5068] Total sum charged with respect to a single line item of an invoice.

code.title: Landing charges
code.desc: The charges incurred in landing the goods into store in the country of importation, excluding Customs duties and taxes.

code.title: Total line items amount
code.desc: The sum of all the line item amounts.

code.title: Licence fees related to imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Licence fees relating to the imported goods that the buyer must pay, either directly or indirectly, as a condition of sale, to the extent that they are not included in the price actually paid or payable.

code.title: Loading and handling cost
code.desc: Cost incurred by loading and handling.

code.title: Lock box total
code.desc: The complete amount of funds that customers mailed in to a specific location. Often times funds are sent to a post-office lock box in their city.

code.title: Lumpsum
code.desc: An agreed sum of money, which is paid in full at one time. This term is often used in connection with charter parties.

code.title: Material consumed in production of imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Value of materials consumed in the production of the imported goods.

code.title: Maximum charge
code.desc: The maximum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

code.title: Message total monetary amount
code.desc: The total of all monetary amounts contained within the message.

code.title: Minimum charge
code.desc: The minimum amount that can be charged for a service or product.

code.title: National preference basis amount
code.desc: Amount giving the basis for national preference calculation.

code.title: Negative collected balance
code.desc: Having a quantity of less than zero in an account.

code.title: Negative ledger balance
code.desc: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a credit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a debit balance.

code.title: Net adjustment
code.desc: The end-of-the-period total amount which is left after recording appropriate adjusting entries.

code.title: Net fee position
code.desc: The payments left over after deductions or allowances have been made.

code.title: Net year to date excess (deficit)
code.desc: A negative amount of an item.

code.title: No amount of insurance
code.desc: No amount of insurance has been declared for a consignment.

code.title: No declared value for carriage
code.desc: No value has been declared for purposes of carriage.

code.title: No declared value for Customs
code.desc: No value has been declared for Customs purposes.

code.title: Quotation total amount
code.desc: [5210] Total monetary amount of a quotation.

code.title: Original amount
code.desc: Original amount, without charges, allowances or adjustment.

code.title: Other charges at destination
code.desc: Code to indicate charges levied at destination.

code.title: Other charges due agent
code.desc: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to an agent.

code.title: Other charges due carrier
code.desc: Code to indicate that certain charges accrue to a carrier.

code.title: Other commissions
code.desc: Other commissions paid by the importer to his/her agent in relation to the goods being imported.

code.title: Other deductible charges
code.desc: Other charges deducted from the total invoice value.

code.title: Other transport charges
code.desc: (5290) Other charges paid for transport.

code.title: Other valuation charges (Customs)
code.desc: Other valuation charges which are payable by reason of the importation or sale of the goods in the Customs territory.

code.title: Packing cost
code.desc: Cost for packing concerning labour and/or material.

code.title: Transport equipment total for customs packing cost amount
code.desc: [5448] Costs incurred for all containers and coverings of whatever nature which are considered as being one for Customs purposes with the goods, and the cost of packing whether for labour or material.

code.title: Parts incorporated in imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Materials, components, parts and similar items incorporated in the imported goods.

code.title: Payment discount amount
code.desc: Discount for paying early.

code.title: Pick-up fee
code.desc: Fee incurring if item has been or will be picked up.

code.title: Positive collected balance
code.desc: Having a quantity of greater than zero in an account.

code.title: Positive ledger balance
code.desc: For an asset account, this would be when the account had a debit balance. For liability and owner's equity accounts, it would be when the account had a credit balance.

code.title: Prepaid amount
code.desc: (5302) Amount which has been prepaid in advance.

code.title: Prepaid charge summary total
code.desc: Total of all prepaid charges.

code.title: Prepaid taxes total
code.desc: Total of all prepaid taxes.

code.title: Purchase amount
code.desc: The cost of buying goods or services.

code.title: Quantity discount
code.desc: Discount given for purchase of goods in bulk.

code.title: Quota value
code.desc: The monetary value of a quota.

code.title: Received amount
code.desc: The amount is what the bank received, and the one before charges/allowances.

code.title: Sales tax
code.desc: Identifies the amount of sales tax payable.

code.title: Shipment value in domestic currency
code.desc: The cost of transportation in domestic currency.

code.title: Specific amount payable
code.desc: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

code.title: Goods item for statistics declared value amount
code.desc: [5218] Value declared for statistical purposes of those goods in a consignment which have the same statistical heading.

code.title: Tax amount
code.desc: Tax imposed by government or other official authority related to the weight/volume charge or valuation charge.

code.title: Taxable amount
code.desc: Amount on which a tax has to be applied.

code.title: To collect
code.desc: Amount that has to be collected.

code.title: Tools used in production of imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Tools, dies, moulds and similar items used in the production of the imported goods.

code.title: Total amount
code.desc: The amount specified is the total amount.

code.title: Total amount subject to payment discount
code.desc: Part of the invoice amount which is subject to payment discount.

code.title: Total charge due
code.desc: Total amount of charges payable to the carrier.

code.title: Total charges/allowances
code.desc: The amount specified is the total of all charges/allowances.

code.title: Total collect charges
code.desc: Total charges to be collected.

code.title: Total collect charges at destination
code.desc: Total charges to be collected at destination.

code.title: Total declared
code.desc: The total value of declared amounts.

code.title: Total freight due
code.desc: Total amount of freight costs payable to the carrier.

code.title: Total invoice additional amount
code.desc: (5140) Amount to be added to the sum of invoice line amounts to arrive at the total invoice amount.

code.title: Damage protection plan coverage
code.desc: Indicates the amount of damage coverage provided under the Damage Protection Plan (DPP).

code.title: Total monetary discount amount
code.desc: Total of monetary discount amounts.

code.title: Total payment amount
code.desc: A complete charge for goods or services rendered.

code.title: Total service charge
code.desc: The complete payment owed to one who has performed work for another.

code.title: Cost, insurance and freight (CIF) value
code.desc: Identifies the value of cost, insurance and freight. (Refer to ICC Incoterm CIF for an expanded definition).

code.title: Trade discount
code.desc: Discount given to any purchaser at a particular commercial level e.g. at wholesale or retail level.

code.title: Transfer amount
code.desc: The amount which has been transferred from buyer to the sellers bank.

code.title: Transport charges (Customs)
code.desc: (5290) Cost incurred by shipper in moving goods, by whatever means, from one place to another under the terms of the contract of carriage, see UN/ECE Recommendation No 23. Synonym: freight charges (Customs).

code.title: Transport charges incurred outside Customs territory
code.desc: (5290) Transport charges incurred outside a Customs territory (or a Customs union).

code.title: Unit price
code.desc: (5110) Reporting monetary amount is a "per unit" amount.

code.title: Acceptable quotation fluctuation amount
code.desc: The maximum increase or decrease in constituent material fluctuation which will not result in an item price renegotiation.

code.title: Total payments under guarantee
code.desc: Total amount paid under guarantee, such as under a factor's guarantee.

code.title: Valuation charge
code.desc: A charge based on the value of goods or cargo.

code.title: Value added tax amount
code.desc: [5490] Amount in national currency resulting from the application, at the appropriate rate, of value added tax (or similar tax) to the invoice amount subject to such tax.

code.title: Consignment insured value amount
code.desc: [5011] Representation in figures of the total sum covered by an insurance for a particular shipment.

code.title: Subsequent resale of imported goods (Customs)
code.desc: Value of any part of the proceeds of any subsequent resale, disposal or use of the imported goods that accrues, directly or indirectly, to the seller.

code.title: Weight charge
code.desc: A charge based on the weight of goods or cargo.

code.title: Amount to be collected
code.desc: The monetary amount that is to be collected.

code.title: Standard duty
code.desc: Standard Customs duty that would apply if special provisions did not apply.

code.title: G-Amount
code.desc: Amount out of total invoice amount being paid into a blocked account.

code.title: Insurance value
code.desc: (5010) Value for which the goods are insured.

code.title: Insurance and transport charges incurred inside Customs territory
code.desc: (5488)+(5290) Charges to be paid for moving goods, by whatever means, from the point of entry into the Customs territory (within a Customs union: to the point of entry in the final destination country).

code.title: Licence (value deducted)
code.desc: Amount in the currency of the licence to be written off from the total licence value.

code.title: Other costs
code.desc: (5346) Costs, other than packing, freight and insurance costs, specified separately.

code.title: Duty, tax or fee amount
code.desc: Amount of duty, tax or fee.

code.title: Customs duty paid
code.desc: Amount which can be deducted from the stated invoice price where that price includes the Customs duty amount.

code.title: Wage tax share
code.desc: Wage tax share of total amount to be paid directly to tax collector.

code.title: Social securities premiums share
code.desc: Social securities share of total amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

code.title: Adjustment amount
code.desc: Amount being the balance of the amount to be adjusted and the adjusted amount.

code.title: Guarantee amount (Customs)
code.desc: Amount of the guarantee placed with Customs.

code.title: Actual versus calculated price difference
code.desc: Difference between actual and calculated price.

code.title: Tax sub-totals
code.desc: A sub total of tax values.

code.title: Alternate currency total amount
code.desc: The total amount as expressed in an alternate currency.

code.title: Document amount
code.desc: The monetary value stated within a related document.

code.title: Total reassignments of factored invoices
code.desc: Total amount of factored invoices and credit notes reassigned to the seller or to another factor.

code.title: Stated amount
code.desc: The monetary amount that has been declared.

code.title: Minimum amount
code.desc: Lowest possible value; minimum.

code.title: Balance brought forward
code.desc: [5190] Opening balance of the account brought forward from the prior accounting period.

code.title: Message total additional amount
code.desc: An amount in addition to the total message value.

code.title: Message total duty/tax/fee amount
code.desc: Total of all duty/tax/fee amounts.

code.title: Message total amount prepaid
code.desc: Total of all prepaid amounts within the message.

code.title: Exact amount
code.desc: Specific amount.

code.title: Maximum amount
code.desc: Highest possible value; maximum.

code.title: Amount up to
code.desc: Highest possible value; up to.

code.title: Amount not exceeding
code.desc: Highest possible value; not exceeding.

code.title: Any other specification/tolerance
code.desc: Any further qualification of the amount.

code.title: No specification/tolerance
code.desc: No further qualification of the amount.

code.title: Final net acquisition cost
code.desc: The final cost of acquisition, net of all add-ons and discounts.

code.title: Labour cost
code.desc: The cost of providing labour to complete a task.

code.title: Material cost
code.desc: The cost of materials needed to complete a task.

code.title: Other cost
code.desc: Non specific costs for an item in addition to those stated explicitly.

code.title: Overhead cost
code.desc: The cost of overhead when completing a task.

code.title: Packaging cost
code.desc: The cost of packaging an item.

code.title: Prototype set up cost
code.desc: The cost of setting up a prototype.

code.title: Authorized cleaning amount
code.desc: Amount of money authorized for cleaning services.

code.title: Raw material per cart cost
code.desc: The cost of raw material expressed per cart.

code.title: Raw material per unit of measure cost
code.desc: The cost of raw material expressed per unit of measure.

code.title: Total die model cost
code.desc: The total of costs for a die model.

code.title: Total gauge cost
code.desc: The total of costs for a gauge.

code.title: Total material including purchased components cost
code.desc: The total cost of materials for an item, including components purchased externally.

code.title: Total purchased components cost
code.desc: The total cost of components purchased externally.

code.title: Total tooling cost
code.desc: The total of costs relating to tooling.

code.title: Delivery limitation amount
code.desc: The monetary limitation amount for a delivery.

code.title: Minimum amount due
code.desc: The minimum amount that must be paid on an amount now due for payment.

code.title: Penalty amount
code.desc: The penalty charge incurred if or because conditions are not met.

code.title: Interest amount
code.desc: The amount of interest charged or paid on a debit or credit balance.

code.title: Line item amount
code.desc: Goods item total minus allowances plus charges for line item. See also Code 66.

code.title: Allowance amount
code.desc: The amount of an allowance.

code.title: Additional amount covered: freight costs
code.desc: Additional amount (freight costs) which is also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amount covered: inspection costs
code.desc: Additional amount (inspection costs) which is also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amount covered: insurance costs
code.desc: Additional amount (insurance costs) which is also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Additional amount covered: interest
code.desc: Additional amount (interest) which is also covered under the documentary credit.

code.title: Agent commission amount
code.desc: Amount which has to be paid to an agent.

code.title: Credit note amount
code.desc: Amount of a credit note.

code.title: Debit note amount
code.desc: Amount of a debit note.

code.title: Documentary credit amount
code.desc: Amount of the documentary credit.

code.title: Part of documentary credit amount
code.desc: Part of documentary credit amount subject to sight payment, deferred payment or acceptance when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

code.title: Advance payment at the beginning of works

code.title: Ceasing contributions

code.title: Mutually defined

code.title: Company additional
code.desc: Additional company payment.

code.title: Company voluntary

code.title: Member additional
code.desc: Additional member payment.

code.title: Group
code.desc: Payment as part of a group plan or scheme.

code.title: Other

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: Mutually defined contribution type.

code.title: Calculation net
code.desc: The price stated is the net price including allowances/ charges. Allowances/charges may be stated for information only.

code.title: Calculation gross
code.desc: The price stated is the gross price to which allowances/ charges must be applied.

code.title: Allowances and charges not included, tax included

code.title: Average selling price
code.desc: Average selling price of a product.

code.title: Information price, excluding allowances or charges, and taxes
code.desc: The price stated is for information purposes only and excludes all allowances, charges and taxes.

code.title: Additive unit price component
code.desc: A code to indicate that the price described is an additive component of the total price.

code.title: Calculation price

code.title: Information

code.title: Invoice price

code.title: Petroleum tax
code.desc: A tax levied on the volume of petroleum being transacted.

code.title: Provisional countervailing duty cash
code.desc: Countervailing duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of subsidization by Customs.

code.title: Provisional countervailing duty bond
code.desc: Countervailing duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on subsidization by Customs.

code.title: Tobacco tax

code.title: Energy fee

code.title: Coffee tax
code.desc: A tax levied specifically on coffee products.

code.title: Harmonised sales tax, Canadian
code.desc: A harmonized sales tax consisting of a goods and service tax, a Canadian provincial sales tax and, as applicable, a Quebec sales tax which is recoverable.

code.title: Quebec sales tax
code.desc: A sales tax charged within the Canadian province of Quebec which is recoverable.

code.title: Canadian provincial sales tax
code.desc: A sales tax charged within Canadian provinces which is non-recoverable.

code.title: Tax on replacement part

code.title: Mineral oil tax

code.title: Anti-dumping duty
code.desc: Duty applied to goods ruled to have been dumped in an import market at a price lower than that in the exporter's domestic market.

code.title: Stamp duty (Imposta di Bollo)

code.title: Agricultural levy
code.desc: Levy imposed on agricultural products where there is a difference between the selling price between trading countries.

code.title: Car tax

code.title: Paper consortium tax (Italy)

code.title: Commodity specific tax

code.title: Customs duty
code.desc: Duties laid down in the Customs tariff, to which goods are liable on entering or leaving the Customs territory (CCC).

code.title: Countervailing duty

code.title: Environmental tax
code.desc: Tax assessed for funding or assuring environmental protection or clean-up.

code.title: Excise duty
code.desc: Customs or fiscal authorities code to identify a specific or ad valorem levy on a specific commodity, applied either domestically or at time of importation.

code.title: Agricultural export rebate
code.desc: Monetary rebate given to the seller in certain circumstances when agricultural products are exported.

code.title: Federal excise tax
code.desc: Tax levied by the federal government on the manufacture of specific items.

code.title: Free
code.desc: No tax levied.

code.title: General construction tax
code.desc: General tax for construction.

code.title: Goods and services tax
code.desc: Tax levied on the final consumption of goods and services throughout the production and distribution chain.

code.title: Illuminants tax
code.desc: Tax of illuminants.

code.title: Import tax
code.desc: Tax assessed on imports.

code.title: Individual tax
code.desc: A tax levied based on an individual's ability to pay.

code.title: Business license fee
code.desc: Government assessed charge for permit to do business.

code.title: Local construction tax
code.desc: Local tax for construction.

code.title: Light dues payable
code.desc: Fee levied on a vessel to pay for port navigation lights.

code.title: Local sales tax
code.desc: Assessment charges on sale of goods or services by city, borough country or other taxing authorities below state or provincial level.

code.title: Lust tax

code.title: Monetary compensatory amount

code.title: Other taxes

code.desc: Anti-dumping duty paid by posting a bond during an investigation period prior to a formal decision on dumping by Customs.

code.title: Provisional duty cash
code.desc: Anti-dumping duty paid in cash prior to a formal finding of dumping by Customs.

code.title: Preference duty

code.title: Special construction tax
code.desc: Special tax for construction.

code.title: Shifted social securities
code.desc: Social securities share of the invoice amount to be paid directly to the social securities collector.

code.title: State/provincial sales tax

code.title: Suspended duty

code.title: Surtax

code.title: Alcohol mark tax

code.title: Total

code.title: Tonnage taxes

code.title: Value added tax

code.title: Commission on delivery

code.title: Confirmation commission
code.desc: Fee for confirmation of credit.

code.title: Deferred payment commission

code.title: Commission for taking up documents

code.title: Opening commission
code.desc: Fee for opening revocable documentary credit.

code.title: Fee for payment under reserve

code.title: Discrepancy fee

code.desc: Fee for the pre-advice of a documentary credit.

code.title: Supervisory commission
code.desc: Fee for the supervising unconfirmed documentary credits with a deferred payment period.

code.title: Model charges

code.title: Risk commission
code.desc: Commission in addition to the confirmation commission for documentary credits from sensitive countries.

code.title: Guarantee commission
code.desc: Commission for drawing up guaranties.

code.title: Reimbursement commission
code.desc: Fee for reimbursement of, for example, documentary credits.

code.title: Stamp duty
code.desc: Tax payable on bills in accordance with national bill of exchange legislation.

code.title: Brokerage

code.title: Bank charges
code.desc: Charges deducted/claimed by other banks involved in the transaction.

code.title: Bank charges information
code.desc: Charges not included in the total charge amount i.e. the charges are for information only.

code.title: Phone fee

code.title: S.W.I.F.T. fee

code.title: Telex fee
code.desc: Fee for telex.

code.title: Project management cost

code.title: Pro rata retention

code.title: Contractual retention

code.title: Other retentions
code.desc: Retention charge not otherwise specified.

code.title: Interest on arrears
code.desc: Interest for late payment.

code.desc: Cost of using money.

code.title: Charge per unused credit cover
code.desc: Unit charge per unused credit cover.

code.title: Minimum commission

code.title: Factoring commission

code.title: Chamber of commerce charge

code.title: Transfer charges

code.desc: Charge for agreed debit interest

code.title: Destination haulage charges

code.title: Disbursement

code.title: Miscellaneous charges

code.title: Origin port charges

code.title: Other charges

code.desc: Amount that the consignor agrees to be invoiced or to pay. This amount is part of the total charges applied to the consignment.

code.title: Transport costs (carriage charges)
code.desc: Monetary amount calculated on the basis of the transport tariffs or contract eventually including charges or other costs.

code.title: All costs up to a specified location
code.desc: All amounts to be paid by the consignor for a part of the voyage, i.e. up to a location that must be precised. (The remaining part of the voyage to be paid by the consignee) The amounts are calculated by the carrier in accordance with tariffs or in case of special events during the voyage (e.g. rail - freight costs - additional costs).

code.title: Weight/valuation charge
code.desc: Code to indicate weight/valuation charges to be either wholly prepaid or wholly collect.

code.title: All costs
code.desc: All cost elements.

code.title: Supply of certificate of shipment

code.title: Supply of consular formalities or certificate of origin
code.desc: Charges payable for the supply of consular formalities or certificate of origin.

code.title: Supply of non-categorised documentation in paper form

code.title: Supply of customs formalities, export

code.title: Supply of customs formalities, transit
code.desc: Charges payable for the supply of transit customs formalities.

code.title: Supply of customs formalities, import
code.desc: Charges payable for the supply of import customs formalities.

code.title: Specific commodity rate
code.desc: Code specifying the specific commodity rate.

code.title: Teenager rate
code.desc: Rate class applies to teenagers.

code.title: Child rate
code.desc: Rate class applies to children.

code.title: Adult rate
code.desc: Rate class applies to adults.

code.title: Rate per kilogram
code.desc: Code specifying the rate per kilogram.

code.title: Minimum charge rate
code.desc: Code specifying the minimum charge rate.

code.title: Normal rate
code.desc: Code specifying the normal rate.

code.title: Quantity rate
code.desc: Code specifying the quantity rate.

code.title: Class rate (Reduction on normal rate)
code.desc: Code specifying the reduction on normal rate.

code.title: Class rate (Surcharge on normal rate)
code.desc: Code specifying the surcharge on normal rate.

code.title: Allowance
code.desc: (5044) Allowance expressed as a percentage.

code.title: Charge
code.desc: (5044) Charge expressed as a percentage.

code.title: Monetary amount adjustment percentage
code.desc: [5044] Specification of any additional charges, dues or deductions, expressed as a percentage.

code.title: Reinsurer's share
code.desc: To indicate the share of the reinsurer in a treaty.

code.title: Entry percentage
code.desc: To indicate the percentage used for the specified entry (e.g. commission %, deposits % ...).

code.title: Quality/yield

code.title: Percentage of invoice
code.desc: Code specifying the percentage of invoice.

code.title: Reduction/surcharge percentage
code.desc: Percentage to calculate a reduction/surcharge.

code.title: Adjustment

code.title: Bureau share

code.title: Buffer stock requirement
code.desc: Anticipated additional consumption to safeguard against unforeseen shortages or demands.

code.title: Discount

code.title: Amount tolerance

code.title: Percentage of note
code.desc: Percentage of debit or credit note.

code.title: Penalty percentage
code.desc: Code specifying the penalty percentage.

code.title: Interest percentage
code.desc: Code specifying the interest percentage.

code.title: Part of documentary credit amount
code.desc: Part of documentary credit amount in percentage subject to sight payment, deferred payment or acceptance when the documentary credit is available by mixed payment.

code.title: Percentage credit note
code.desc: Percentage of a credit note.

code.title: Percentage debit note
code.desc: Percentage of a debit note.

code.title: Percentage of insurance
code.desc: Code specifying the percentage of insurance.

code.title: Own risk percentage
code.desc: Percentage of total amount which is not covered by credit cover.

code.title: Transferred VAT percentage
code.desc: VAT percentage rate for which accountability is being transferred from one party to another. VAT means: Value added tax.

code.title: Part time employment

code.title: Voluntary contribution

code.title: Attribute factor

code.title: Additional contribution

code.title: Benefits allocation

code.title: Attribute classification
code.desc: To indicate the percentage of a specified attribute classification (e.g. percentage contributed before a defined year for superannuation purposes).

code.title: Volume capacity usage

code.title: Weight capacity usage

code.title: Loading length capacity usage

code.title: Share of packaging cost paid by vendor

code.title: Reduction percentage
code.desc: Reduction from an amount/price expressed in a percentage.

code.title: Blocks
code.desc: A piece of equipment that is normally a piece of wood to fix cargo (e.g. coils) during transport.

code.title: Box pallet non-exchangeable
code.desc: A box pallet which cannot be exchanged.

code.title: Truck being transported
code.desc: A road vehicle capable of carrying goods which is being carried on another means of transport.

code.title: Truck and trailer combination being transported
code.desc: A road vehicle capable of carrying goods with an attached trailer which is being carried on another means of transport.

code.title: Tractor and trailer being transported
code.desc: A trailer accompanied by a self-propelling tractor unit which is being carried on another means of transport.

code.title: Postal bag
code.desc: Bag intended primarily for the conveyance of postal items.

code.title: Letter Tray
code.desc: Tray intended primarily for the conveyance of letter mail items of size slightly exceeding C5, in which the items are stood on their long edge.

code.title: Roller Cage
code.desc: Wheeled wire cage.

code.title: Flats Tray
code.desc: Tray intended primarily for the conveyance of letter mail items of from C5 up to in excess of C4, in which the items are stacked one on top of another. May also be used for letter mail smaller items stood on their long edge.

code.title: Out of bag parcel
code.desc: Postal item which is conveyed individually, with only the wrapping provided by the mailer for protection.

code.title: Wheeled Platform
code.desc: Device, consisting of a flat surface mounted on a wheels, which is designed for the conveyance of items which may safely be stacked. Normally also equipped with a handle to allow the device to be easily manoeuvred.

code.title: Container non-compliant with the Customs Convention on Containers
code.desc: The container is not compliant with the Customs Convention on Containers.

code.title: Box pallet EUR Y non exchangeable
code.desc: A euro-pallet of type Y that may not be exchanged.

code.title: Barge
code.desc: Flat bottomed inland cargo vessel for canals and rivers with or without own propulsion for the purpose of transported goods. (Synonym: Lighter).

code.title: Boxcar
code.desc: An enclosed railway goods wagon.

code.title: Chassis
code.desc: A wheeled carriage onto which an ocean container is mounted for inland conveyance.

code.title: Container
code.desc: Equipment item as defined by ISO for transport. It must be of: A) permanent character, strong enough for repeated use; B) designed to facilitate the carriage of goods, by one or more modes of transport, without intermediate reloading; C) fitted with devices for its ready handling, particularly.

code.title: Deadlight (panel)
code.desc: A set of panels fixed inside a porthole.

code.title: Exchangeable EUR flat pallet
code.desc: A flat euro-pallet that may be exchanged.

code.title: Exchangeable EUR Y box pallet
code.desc: A euro-pallet of type Y that may be exchanged.

code.title: Flat pallet EUR non exchangeable
code.desc: A flat euro-pallet that may not be exchanged.

code.title: Flat pallet (railway property) non-exchangeable
code.desc: A non-exchangeable flat pallet owned by a railroad.

code.title: Lidded stackable rigid tray (CEN TS 14482:2002)
code.desc: Lidded stackable rigid tray compliant with CEN TS 14482:2002.

code.title: Lashing rope
code.desc: A rope for lashing cargo.

code.title: Load/unload device on equipment
code.desc: A mechanical device used in the loading and/or unloading of cargo into and from transport equipment.

code.title: Movable panel
code.desc: A panel which can be moved.

code.title: Pallet
code.desc: A platform on which goods can be stacked in order to facilitate the movement by a forklift or sling.

code.title: Identified private box pallet
code.desc: A box pallet identified as being privately owned.

code.title: Identified private flat pallet
code.desc: A flat pallet identified as being privately owned.

code.title: Platform
code.desc: A piece of equipment normally having a flat surface, or prepared for carrying cargo with a specific shape.

code.title: Protecting panel
code.desc: A panel used for protection.

code.title: Portable stove
code.desc: A portable heating unit.

code.title: Flat car
code.desc: A railway wagon without raised sides or ends.

code.title: Reefer generator
code.desc: A generator used to control the temperature in temperature-controlled transport equipment.

code.title: Ground facility
code.desc: Storage tank or facility capable of receiving shipment of goods or commodity.

code.title: Rope
code.desc: Rope used in the securing of cargo.

code.title: Rail car
code.desc: To identify that the equipment is a rail car.

code.title: Identified special pallet
code.desc: A pallet identified as special.

code.title: Strap
code.desc: A narrow strip of flexible material.

code.title: Swap body
code.desc: Rectangular equipment unit without wheels, which can be mounted on a chassis or positioned on legs.

code.title: Trailer
code.desc: A vehicle without motive power, designed for the carriage of cargo and to be towed by a motor vehicle.

code.title: Tarpaulin
code.desc: Waterproof material, e.g. canvas, to spread over cargo to protect it from getting wet.

code.title: Tackles
code.desc: Identification of loading tackle used (sheets, ropes, chains, etc.), as specified in DCU 9 to CIM Article 13; and of containers, as specified in Articles 5 and 10 of Annex III to CIM (CIM 17).

code.title: Tarpaulin support
code.desc: A device to support a tarpaulin.

code.title: ULD (Unit load device)
code.desc: An aircraft container or pallet.

code.title: Shipper supplied
code.desc: The transport equipment is supplied by the shipper.

code.title: Carrier supplied
code.desc: The transport equipment is supplied by the carrier.

code.title: Consolidator supplied
code.desc: The equipment is supplied by the consolidator.

code.title: Deconsolidator supplied
code.desc: The equipment is supplied by the deconsolidator.

code.title: Third party supplied
code.desc: The equipment is supplied by a third party.

code.title: Forwarder supplied from a leasing company
code.desc: The equipment is supplied by the forwarder and is taken from a leasing company.

code.title: Forwarder supplied from the railways' pool

code.title: Buyer to seller
code.desc: The transport from the buyer to the seller.

code.title: Seller to buyer
code.desc: The transport from the seller to the buyer.

code.title: Subcontractor to seller
code.desc: The transport from the subcontractor to the seller.

code.title: Seller to drop ship designated location
code.desc: The transport from the seller to the drop ship designated location.

code.title: Seller to freight forwarder
code.desc: The transport from the seller to the freight forwarder.

code.title: Seller to subcontractor
code.desc: The transport from the seller to the subcontractor.

code.title: Mother vessel to lighter
code.desc: Cargo is transferred from the main carriage or mother vessel to a lighter.

code.title: Lighter to mother vessel
code.desc: Cargo is transferred from the lighter vessel to a main carriage or mother vessel.

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

code.title: Dime coated tank
code.desc: A tank coated with dime.

code.title: Epoxy coated tank
code.desc: A tank coated with epoxy.

code.title: Pressurized tank
code.desc: A tank capable of holding pressurized goods.

code.title: Refrigerated tank
code.desc: A tank capable of keeping goods refrigerated.

code.title: Stainless steel tank
code.desc: A tank made of stainless steel.

code.title: Trailer
code.desc: Non self-propelled vehicle designed for the carriage of cargo so that it can be towed by a motor vehicle.

code.title: Nonworking reefer container 20 ft
code.desc: A 20 foot refrigerated container that is not actively controlling temperature of the product.

code.title: Exchangeable pallet
code.desc: Standard pallet exchangeable following international convention.

code.title: Semi-trailer
code.desc: Non self propelled vehicle without front wheels designed for the carriage of cargo and provided with a kingpin.

code.desc: A tank container with a length of 30 feet.

code.desc: A tank container with a length of 40 feet.

code.title: Container IC 40 feet
code.desc: A container owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 40 feet.

code.title: Refrigerated tank 20 feet

code.title: Refrigerated tank 30 feet
code.desc: A refrigerated tank with a length of 30 feet.

code.title: Refrigerated tank 40 feet
code.desc: A refrigerated tank with a length of 40 feet.

code.title: Tank container IC 20 feet
code.desc: A tank container owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 20 feet.

code.title: Tank container IC 30 feet
code.desc: A tank container owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 30 feet.

code.title: Tank container IC 40 feet
code.desc: A tank container, owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 40 feet.

code.desc: A refrigerated tank owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 20 feet.

code.title: Temperature controlled container 30 ft.

code.title: Refrigerated tank IC 40 feet
code.desc: A refrigerated tank owned by InterContainer, a European railway subsidiary, with a length of 40 feet.

code.title: Movable case: L < 6,15m
code.desc: A movable case with a length less than 6,15 metres.

code.title: Movable case: 6,15m < L < 7,82m
code.desc: A movable case with a length between 6,15 metres and 7,82 metres.

code.desc: A movable case with a length between 7,82 metres and 9,15 metres.

code.desc: A movable case with a length between 9,15 metres and 10,90 metres.

code.desc: Temperature controlled container measuring 20 feet.

code.title: Temperature controlled container 40 ft
code.desc: A temperature controlled container measuring 40 feet.

code.title: Non working refrigerated (reefer) container 30ft.
code.desc: A 30 foot refrigerated (reefer) container that is not actively cooling the product.

code.title: Dual trailers
code.desc: Two trailers linked together one behind another and pulled by one tractor.

code.title: 20 ft IL container (open top)
code.desc: An open top container that is 20 feet in internal length.

code.title: 20 ft IL container (closed top)
code.desc: A closed top container that is 20 feet in internal length.

code.title: 40 ft IL container (closed top)
code.desc: A closed top container that is 40 feet in internal length.

code.title: More than one quarter volume available
code.desc: Indicates that there is more than a quarter of the volume available.

code.title: More than half volume available
code.desc: Indicates that there is more than a half of the volume available.

code.title: More than three quarters volume available
code.desc: Indicates that there is more than three quarters of the volume available.

code.title: Empty
code.desc: Indicates that the object is empty.

code.title: Full
code.desc: Indicates that the object is full.

code.title: No volume available
code.desc: Indicates that there is no space available in the object.

code.title: Full, mixed consignment
code.desc: Indicates that the equipment is fully loaded, and includes a number LCL (Less Than Container Load) consignments.

code.title: Full, single consignment
code.desc: Indicates that the container is fully loaded with a single FCL (Full Container Load) consignment.

code.title: Part load
code.desc: Container represents part of a consignment declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. the Customs declaration covers more than one container).

code.title: Part load mixed consignments
code.desc: Container represents part of the consignment declared on a single Customs declaration with the remainder being in other containers. Other goods, related to other declarations, are also in the container.

code.title: Single invoiced load
code.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by a single invoice.

code.title: Multi invoiced load
code.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by more than one invoice.

code.title: Full load, multiple bills
code.desc: A container representing a consignment of goods for one consignee with multiple bill of lading numbers.

code.title: Continental
code.desc: The equipment is or will be moving across a continent on an intermodal or multimodal basis.

code.title: Export
code.desc: Transport equipment to be exported on a marine vessel.

code.title: Import
code.desc: Transport equipment to be imported on a marine vessel.

code.title: Remain on board
code.desc: Transport equipment arriving on a marine vessel is to remain on board.

code.title: Shifter
code.desc: Transport equipment is to be shifted from one stowage location on a marine vessel to another on the same vessel.

code.title: Transhipment
code.desc: Transport equipment is to be transferred from one marine vessel to another.

code.title: Shortlanded
code.desc: Transport equipment notified to arrive which did not arrive on the means of transport.

code.title: Overlanded
code.desc: Transport equipment not notified to arrive but which did arrive on the means of transport.

code.title: Domestic
code.desc: Transport equipment is used in domestic service.

code.title: Positioning
code.desc: Equipment is being transported for positioning purposes.

code.title: Delivery
code.desc: Equipment is being delivered.

code.title: Redelivery
code.desc: Equipment is being redelivered.

code.title: Repair
code.desc: The equipment is for repair.

code.title: Reloader
code.desc: Transport equipment to be discharged and subsequently reloaded on the same means of transport but in a different stowage location.

code.title: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road (ADR)
code.desc: European agreement on the international carriage of dangerous goods on road. ADR is the abbreviation of "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par route".

code.title: NDR European agreement for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine
code.desc: European agreement giving regulations for the transport of dangerous goods on the river Rhine, officially known as: "Accord europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises dangereuses par navigation sur le Rhin.".

code.title: CA, Transport Canada's dangerous goods requirements
code.desc: Canadian transport of dangerous goods requirements as published by Transport Canada in the Canadian Gazette, Part II.

code.title: JP, Japanese maritime safety agency dangerous goods regulation code
code.desc: Regulation regarding the handling of dangerous goods on vessels issued by Japanese maritime safety agency.

code.title: MARPOL 73/78
code.desc: International Convention for the Prevention of Pollution from Ships, 1973, as modified by the Protocol of 1978 relating.

code.title: DE, ADR and GGVS combined regulations for combined transport
code.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au Transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse.

code.title: ADNR, Autorisation de transport de matieres Dangereuses pour la Navigation sur le Rhin
code.desc: Regulations for dangerous goods transportation on the Rhine.

code.title: DE, ARD and RID - Combined regulations for combined transport
code.desc: Combined European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on roads and rails. ARD means: Autorisation de transport par Route de matieres dangereuses. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer.

code.title: US, 49 Code of federal regulations
code.desc: United States federal regulations issued by the US Department of transportation covering the domestic transportation of dangerous goods by truck, rail, water and air.

code.title: DE, ADR, RID, GGVS and GGVE - Combined regulations for combined transport
code.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the combined transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European roads and rails. ADR means: Accord Europeen relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuse par Route. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVS means: Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

code.title: DE, GGVE (Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn)
code.desc: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on rail.

code.title: DE, GGVS (Gefahrgutverordnung Strasse)
code.desc: German regulation for the transportation of dangerous goods on road.

code.title: IATA ICAO
code.desc: Regulations covering the international transportation of dangerous goods issued by the International Air Transport Association and the International Civil Aviation Organization.

code.title: IMO IMDG code
code.desc: Regulations regarding the transportation of dangerous goods on ocean-going vessels issued by the International Maritime Organization.

code.title: DE, RID and GGVE, Combined regulations for combined transport on rails
code.desc: Combined German and European regulations for the transportation of dangerous goods on German and other European rails. RID means: Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer. GGVE means: Gefahrgutverordnung Eisenbahn.

code.title: Railroad dangerous goods book (RID)
code.desc: International regulations concerning the international carriage of dangerous goods by rail. RID is the abbreviation of "Reglement International concernant le transport des marchandises Dangereuses par chemin de fer".

code.title: UK IMO book
code.desc: The United Kingdom (UK) version of the International Maritime Organisation (IMO) book on dangerous goods.

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: Additional and/or other information for the transportation of dangerous goods which are mutually defined.

code.title: Full load
code.desc: Container represents the full consignment of goods declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. all goods in the container relate to a single Customs declaration).

code.title: Part load
code.desc: Container represents part of a consignment declared on a single Customs declaration (i.e. the Customs declaration covers more than one container).

code.title: Full load mixed consignments
code.desc: Container holds the full consignment related to the Customs declaration but also holds goods related to other declarations.

code.title: Part load mixed consignments
code.desc: Container represents part of the consignment declared on a single Customs declaration with the remainder being in other containers. Other goods, related to other declarations, are also in the container.

code.title: Single invoiced load
code.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by a single invoice.

code.title: Multi invoiced load
code.desc: Merchandise within a container/package covered by more than one invoice.

code.title: Empty
code.desc: Container holds no goods.

code.title: Full load, multiple bills
code.desc: A container representing a consignment of goods for one consignee with multiple bill of lading numbers.

code.title: Transport for the owner's account
code.desc: The owner of the transported goods is also the owner of the means of transport or rented it for this transport.

code.title: Transport for another account
code.desc: The owner of the transported goods does not own the means of transport or has not rented it for this transport.

code.title: Private transport
code.desc: A code indicating privately owned transport.

code.title: Export
code.desc: The transport movement is to export the goods from the country.

code.title: Import
code.desc: The transport movement is to import the goods into the country.

code.title: Transit
code.desc: The cargo is moving in transit through a country and will not become part of the commerce of that country.

code.title: Relay
code.desc: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession under the responsibility of the same carrier.

code.title: Transshipment
code.desc: The cargo is being moved by more than one transport means in succession.

code.title: Breakbulk
code.desc: Defines the movement of general cargo not carried in ISO standard containers.

code.title: LCL/LCL
code.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed in and unpacked from containers by the carrier on behalf of the shipper/consignee. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

code.title: FCL/FCL
code.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'FCL' means Full Container Load.

code.title: FCL/LCL
code.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the shipper or shipper's agent and unpacked by the carrier. 'FCL' means Full Container Load. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load.

code.title: LCL/FCL
code.desc: Defines the movement of cargo packed by the carrier and unpacked by the consignee or consignee's agent. 'LCL' means Less than Container Load. 'FCL' means Full Load.

code.title: Consolidation
code.desc: A movement of multiple shipments to a single destination.

code.title: Parcel post
code.desc: A movement of material by parcel post.

code.title: Expedited truck
code.desc: A movement of material by expedited truck.

code.title: Consignor determined means
code.desc: A movement of material by the means determined by the consignor.

code.title: Private parcel service
code.desc: A movement of material by a private parcel service.

code.title: House to house
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

code.title: House to terminal
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked at the carrier's inland facility between the ship's point of discharge and the final destination.

code.title: House to pier
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit by the shipper at point of origin and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

code.title: Air charter
code.desc: A movement of material by chartered aircraft.

code.title: Air express
code.desc: A movement of material by air express service.

code.title: Geographic grouped transport
code.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to a single destination utilizing a single carrier and a single freight bill.

code.title: Less than truck load
code.desc: A movement of material on a truck that is not full.

code.title: Pooled piggyback
code.desc: A movement of material by a trailer on a railcar.

code.title: Consignee transportation provided
code.desc: A movement of material transported by the consignee.

code.title: Rail
code.desc: A movement of material to the consignee via rail.

code.title: Terminal to house
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and the ship's point of loading and unpacked by consignee at the final destination.

code.title: Terminal to terminal
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and the ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

code.title: Terminal to pier
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at a carrier's inland facility between point of origin and ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

code.title: Pier to house
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by consignee at final destination.

code.title: Pier to terminal
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked at a carrier's inland facility between ship's point of discharge and final destination.

code.title: Pier to pier
code.desc: Cargo packed in a unit at ship's point of loading and unpacked by carrier at ship's point of discharge (pier).

code.title: Station to station
code.desc: The consignment is moving from one container freight station to another container freight station.

code.title: House to warehouse
code.desc: The consignment is moving from the premises of the shipper to a warehouse.

code.title: Warehouse to house
code.desc: The consignment is moving from a warehouse to the premises of the consignee.

code.title: Station to house
code.desc: The cargo is moving from a container freight station to the premises of the consignee.

code.title: Geographic grouped transport, multiple origins, multiple destinations
code.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to multiple destinations using a single carrier and a single freight bill.

code.title: Geographic grouped transport, multiple origins, single destination
code.desc: A movement of material from multiple origins to a single destination utilizing a single carrier and a single freight bill.

code.title: Geographic receiving
code.desc: A collection of shipments that involve a single origin, multiple destinations, and a single trailer, and are paid under a single freight bill.

code.title: Great danger

code.title: Medium danger
code.desc: Packaging meeting criteria to pack hazardous materials with medium danger. Group II according to IATA/IDMG/ADR/RID regulations.

code.title: Minor danger
code.desc: Packaging meeting criteria to pack hazardous materials with minor danger. Group III according to IATA/IDMG/ADR/RID regulations.

code.title: Not assigned
code.desc: No packaging danger level has been assigned.

code.title: Carrier
code.desc: Haulage arranged by carrier.

code.title: Merchant
code.desc: Haulage arranged by merchant (shipper, consignee, or their agent).

code.title: Loaded with empty 4-block for blocking purposes
code.desc: Loaded with empty 4-block for blocking purposes.

code.title: Empty container with dunnage
code.desc: The container is, has been, or will be returned with dunnage only.

code.title: Empty container
code.desc: The container is, has been, or will be returned empty.

code.title: Loaded with production material
code.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with production material.

code.title: Obsolete material
code.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with obsolete material.

code.title: Loaded with excess returned production material
code.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with excess production material.

code.title: Loaded with rejected material
code.desc: The package is, has been, or will be returned loaded with rejected material.

code.title: Loaded with returned processed material

code.title: Mutually defined
code.desc: A code assigned within a code list to be used on an interim basis and as defined among trading partners until a precise code can be assigned to the code list.

code.title: Engineering change or late release
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to engineering change or late release.

code.title: Specification (schedule) error/overbuilding

code.title: Shipment tracing delay
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to shipment tracing delay.

code.title: Plant inventory loss
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to plant inventory loss.

code.title: Building ahead of schedule
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to building ahead of schedule.

code.title: Vendor behind schedule
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to vendor behind schedule.

code.title: Failed to include in last shipment
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to failure to include costs in last shipment.

code.title: Carrier loss claim
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to carrier loss claim.

code.title: Transportation failure
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to transportation failure.

code.title: Insufficient weight for carload
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to insufficient weight for carload.

code.title: Reject or discrepancy (material rejected in prior shipment)
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to reject or discrepancy.

code.title: Transportation delay
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to transportation delay.

code.title: Lack of railcar or railroad equipment
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to lack of railcar of railroad equipment.

code.title: Releasing error
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to releasing error.

code.title: Record error or cate reported discrepancy report
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to record error or cate reported discrepancy report.

code.title: Common or peculiar part schedule increase
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to common or peculiar part schedule increase.

code.title: Alternative supplier shipping for responsible supplier
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to alternative supplier shipping for responsible supplier.

code.title: Direct schedule or locally controlled
code.desc: The reason for the excess transportation is due to direct schedule or locally controlled.

code.title: Purchasing waiver approval
